quran[842]{c,v,t}:
  37,1,By those ЋєangelsЋЇ lined up in ranks
  37,2,and those who diligently drive Ћєthe cloudsЋЇ
  37,3,and those who recite the Reminder
  37,4,Surely your God is One
  37,5,"ЋєHe isЋЇ the Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between, and the Lord of all points of sunrise"
  37,6,"Indeed, We have adorned the lowest heaven with the stars for decoration"
  37,7,and ЋєforЋЇ protection from every rebellious devil
  37,8,They cannot listen to the highest assembly Ћєof angelsЋЇ for they are pelted from every side
  37,9,ЋєfiercelyЋЇ driven away. And they will suffer an everlasting torment
  37,10,But whoever manages to stealthily eavesdrop is ЋєinstantlyЋЇ pursued by a piercing flare
  37,11,"So ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, which is harder to create: them or other marvels of Our creation?¬†Indeed, We created them from a sticky clay"
  37,12,"In fact, you are astonished Ћєby their denialЋЇ, while they ridicule ЋєyouЋЇ"
  37,13,"When they are reminded, they are never mindful"
  37,14,"And whenever they see a sign, they make fun of it"
  37,15,"saying, вАЬThis is nothing but pure magic"
  37,16,"When we are dead and reduced to dust and bones, will we really be resurrected"
  37,17,And our forefathers as well?вАЭ
  37,18,"Say, вАЬYes! And you will be fully humbled.вАЭ"
  37,19,"It will only take one Blast,¬†then at once they will see Ћєit allЋЇ"
  37,20,"They will cry, вАЬOh, woe to us! This is the Day of Judgment!вАЭ"
  37,21,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬThis is the Day of ЋєFinalЋЇ Decision which you used to deny.вАЭ"
  37,22,"ЋєGod will say to the angels,ЋЇ вАЬGather ЋєallЋЇ the wrongdoers along with their peers, and whatever they used to worship"
  37,23,"instead of God, then lead them ЋєallЋЇ to the path of Hell"
  37,24,"And detain them, for they must be questioned.вАЭ"
  37,25,"ЋєThen they will be asked,ЋЇ вАЬWhat is the matter with you that you can no longer help each other?вАЭ"
  37,26,"In fact, on that Day they will be ЋєfullyЋЇ submissive"
  37,27,"They will turn on each other, throwing blame"
  37,28,"The misled will say, вАЬIt was you who deluded us away from what is right.вАЭ"
  37,29,"The misleaders will reply, вАЬNo! You disbelieved on your own"
  37,30,"We had no authority over you. In fact, you yourselves were a transgressing people"
  37,31,"The decree of our Lord has come to pass against us ЋєallЋЇ: we will certainly taste Ћєthe punishmentЋЇ"
  37,32,"We caused you to deviate, for we ourselves were deviant.вАЭ"
  37,33,Surely on that Day they will ЋєallЋЇ share in the punishment
  37,34,That is certainly how We deal with the wicked
  37,35,"For whenever it was said to them Ћєin the worldЋЇ, вАЬThere is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except God,вАЭ they acted arrogantly"
  37,36,"and argued, вАЬShould we really abandon our gods for a mad poet?вАЭ"
  37,37,"In fact, he came with the truth, confirming ЋєearlierЋЇ messengers"
  37,38,You will certainly taste the painful torment
  37,39,and will only be rewarded for what you used to do
  37,40,But not the chosen servants of God
  37,41,They will have a known provision
  37,42,fruits Ћєof every typeЋЇ.¬†And they will be honoured
  37,43,in the Gardens of Bliss
  37,44,facing each other on thrones
  37,45,A drink Ћєof pure wineЋЇ will be passed around to them from a flowing stream
  37,46,"crystal-white, delicious to drink"
  37,47,"It will neither harm ЋєthemЋЇ, nor will they be intoxicated by it"
  37,48,And with them will be maidens of modest gaze and gorgeous eyes
  37,49,as if they were pristine pearls
  37,50,Then they will turn to one another inquisitively
  37,51,"One of them will say, вАЬI once had a companion Ћєin the worldЋЇ"
  37,52,"who used to ask ЋєmeЋЇ, вАШDo you actually believe Ћєin resurrectionЋЇ"
  37,53,"When we are dead and reduced to dust and bones, will we really be brought to judgment?вАЩвАЭ"
  37,54,"He will ЋєthenЋЇ ask, вАЬWould you care to see Ћєhis fateЋЇ?вАЭ"
  37,55,Then he Ћєand the othersЋЇ will look and spot him in the midst of the Hellfire
  37,56,"He will ЋєthenЋЇ say, вАЬBy God! You nearly ruined me"
  37,57,"Had it not been for the grace of my Lord, I ЋєtooЋЇ would have certainly been among those brought Ћєto HellЋЇ.вАЭ"
  37,58,"ЋєThen he will ask his fellow believers,ЋЇ вАЬCan you imagine that we will never die"
  37,59,"except our first death, nor be punished Ћєlike the othersЋЇ?вАЭ"
  37,60,This is truly the ultimate triumph
  37,61,For such ЋєhonourЋЇ all should strive
  37,62,Is this ЋєblissЋЇ a better accommodation or the tree of Zaqq√їm
  37,63,We have surely made it a test for the wrongdoers
  37,64,"Indeed, it is a tree that grows in the depths of Hell"
  37,65,bearing fruit like devilsвАЩ heads
  37,66,"The evildoers will certainly Ћєbe left toЋЇ eat from it, filling up their bellies with it"
  37,67,Then on top of that they will be given a blend of boiling drink
  37,68,Then they will ultimately return to Ћєtheir place inЋЇ Hell
  37,69,"Indeed, they found their forefathers astray"
  37,70,so they rushed in their footsteps
  37,71,And surely most of the earlier generations had strayed before them
  37,72,although We had certainly sent warners among them
  37,73,See then what was the end of those who had been warned
  37,74,But not the chosen servants of God
  37,75,"Indeed, Noah cried out to Us, and how excellent are We in responding"
  37,76,We delivered him and his family¬†from the great distress
  37,77,and made his descendants the sole survivors
  37,78,And We blessed him Ћєwith honourable mentionЋЇ among later generations
  37,79,вАЬPeace be upon Noah among all peoples.вАЭ
  37,80,"Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,81,ЋєForЋЇ he was truly one of Our faithful servants
  37,82,Then We drowned the others
  37,83,"And indeed, one of those who followed his way was Abraham"
  37,84,ЋєRememberЋЇ when he came to his Lord with a pure heart
  37,85,"and said to his father and his people, вАЬWhat are you worshipping"
  37,86,Is it false gods that you desire instead of God
  37,87,What then do you expect from the Lord of all worlds?вАЭ
  37,88,He later looked up to the stars Ћєin contemplationЋЇ
  37,89,"then said, вАЬI am really sick.вАЭ"
  37,90,So they turned their backs on him and went away
  37,91,"Then he ЋєstealthilyЋЇ advanced towards their gods, and said ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWill you not eat Ћєyour offeringsЋЇ"
  37,92,What is wrong with you that you cannot speak?вАЭ
  37,93,"Then he swiftly turned on them, striking ЋєthemЋЇ with his right hand"
  37,94,"Later, his people came rushing towards him ЋєfuriouslyЋЇ"
  37,95,"He argued, вАЬHow can you worship what you carve Ћєwith your own handsЋЇ"
  37,96,when it is God Who created you and whatever you do?вАЭ
  37,97,"They said Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬBuild him a furnace and cast him into the blazing fire.вАЭ"
  37,98,"And so they sought to harm him, but We made them inferior"
  37,99,"He later said, вАЬI am leaving Ћєin obedienceЋЇ to my Lord. He will guide me"
  37,100,My Lord! Bless me with righteous offspring.вАЭ
  37,101,So We gave him good news of a forbearing son
  37,102,"Then when the boy reached the age to work with him, Abraham said, вАЬO my dear son! I have seen in a dream that I ЋєmustЋЇ sacrifice you. So tell me what you think.вАЭ He replied, вАЬO my dear father! Do as you are commanded. God willing, you will find me steadfast.вАЭ"
  37,103,"Then when they submitted Ћєto GodвАЩs WillЋЇ, and Abraham laid him on the side of his forehead Ћєfor sacrificeЋЇ"
  37,104,"We called out to him, вАЬO Abraham"
  37,105,"You have already fulfilled the vision.вАЭ Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,106,That was truly a revealing test
  37,107,And We ransomed his son with a great sacrifice
  37,108,and blessed Abraham Ћєwith honourable mentionЋЇ among later generations
  37,109,вАЬPeace be upon Abraham.вАЭ
  37,110,This is how We reward the good-doers
  37,111,He was truly one of Our faithful servants
  37,112,"We ЋєlaterЋЇ gave him good news of IsaacвАФa prophet, and one of the righteous"
  37,113,"We blessed him¬†and Isaac as well. Some of their descendants did good, while others clearly wronged themselves"
  37,114,And We certainly showed favour to Moses and Aaron
  37,115,and delivered them and their people from the great distress
  37,116,We helped them so it was they who prevailed
  37,117,We gave them the clear Scripture
  37,118,and guided them to the Straight Path
  37,119,And We blessed them Ћєwith honourable mentionЋЇ among later generations
  37,120,вАЬPeace be upon Moses and Aaron.вАЭ
  37,121,"Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,122,They were truly ЋєtwoЋЇ of Our faithful servants
  37,123,And Elias was indeed one of the messengers
  37,124,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when he said to his people, вАЬWill you not fear ЋєGodЋЇ"
  37,125,Do you call upon Ћєthe idol ofЋЇ BaвАЩl¬†and abandon the Best of CreatorsвАФ
  37,126,"God, your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers?вАЭ"
  37,127,"But they rejected him, so they will certainly be brought Ћєfor punishmentЋЇ"
  37,128,But not the chosen servants of God
  37,129,We blessed him Ћєwith honourable mentionЋЇ among later generations
  37,130,вАЬPeace be upon Elias.вАЭ
  37,131,"Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,132,He was truly one of Our faithful servants
  37,133,And Lot was indeed one of the messengers
  37,134,ЋєRememberЋЇ when We delivered him and all of his family
  37,135,"except an old woman,¬†who was one of the doomed"
  37,136,Then We ЋєutterlyЋЇ destroyed the rest
  37,137,You ЋєMeccansЋЇ certainly pass by their ruins day
  37,138,and night. Will you not then understand
  37,139,And Jonah was indeed one of the messengers
  37,140,ЋєRememberЋЇ when he fled to the overloaded ship
  37,141,"Then Ћєto save it from sinking,ЋЇ he drew straws Ћєwith other passengersЋЇ. He lost Ћєand was thrown overboardЋЇ"
  37,142,Then the whale engulfed him while he was blameworthy
  37,143,Had he not ЋєconstantlyЋЇ glorified ЋєGodЋЇ
  37,144,he would have certainly remained in its belly until the Day of Resurrection
  37,145,"But We cast him onto the open ЋєshoreЋЇ, ЋєtotallyЋЇ worn out"
  37,146,and caused a squash plant to grow over him
  37,147,We ЋєlaterЋЇ sent him ЋєbackЋЇ to Ћєhis city ofЋЇ at least one hundred thousand people
  37,148,"who then believed Ћєin himЋЇ, so We allowed them enjoyment for a while"
  37,149,"Ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ if your Lord has daughters,¬†while the pagans Ћєprefer toЋЇ have sons"
  37,150,Or Ћєask themЋЇ if We created the angels as females right before their eyes
  37,151,"Indeed, it is one of their ЋєoutrageousЋЇ fabrications to say"
  37,152,вАЬGod has children.вАЭ They are simply liars
  37,153,Has He chosen daughters over sons
  37,154,What is the matter with you? How do you judge
  37,155,Will you not then be mindful
  37,156,Or do you have ЋєanyЋЇ compelling proof
  37,157,"Then bring ЋєusЋЇ your scripture, if what you say is true"
  37,158,They have also established a ЋєmaritalЋЇ relationship between Him and the jinn. Yet the jinn ЋєthemselvesЋЇ know well that such people will certainly be brought Ћєfor punishmentЋЇ
  37,159,Glorified is God far above what they claim
  37,160,But not the chosen servants of God
  37,161,Surely you ЋєpagansЋЇ and whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you worship
  37,162,can never lure ЋєanyoneЋЇ away from Him
  37,163,except those ЋєdestinedЋЇ to burn in Hell
  37,164,"ЋєThe angels respond,ЋЇ вАЬThere is not one of us without an assigned station Ћєof worshipЋЇ"
  37,165,We are indeed the ones lined up in ranks Ћєfor GodЋЇ
  37,166,And we are indeed the ones ЋєconstantlyЋЇ glorifying ЋєHis praiseЋЇ.вАЭ
  37,167,They certainly used to say
  37,168,вАЬIf only we had a Reminder like Ћєthose ofЋЇ earlier peoples
  37,169,we would have truly been GodвАЩs devoted servants.вАЭ
  37,170,"But ЋєnowЋЇ they reject it, so they will soon know"
  37,171,"Our Word has already gone forth to Our servants, the messengers"
  37,172,that they would surely be helped
  37,173,and that Our forces will certainly prevail
  37,174,So turn away from the deniers for a while ЋєO ProphetЋЇ
  37,175,"You will see Ћєwhat will happen toЋЇ them, and they too will see"
  37,176,Do they ЋєreallyЋЇ wish to hasten Our punishment
  37,177,"Yet when it descends upon them:¬†how evil will that morning be for those who had been warned"
  37,178,And turn away from them for a while
  37,179,"You will see, and they too will see"
  37,180,Glorified is your LordвАФthe Lord of Honour and PowerвАФabove what they claim
  37,181,Peace be upon the messengers
  37,182,And praise be to GodвАФLord of all worlds
  38,1,"бєҐ√£d. By the Quran, full of reminders"
  38,2,"ЋєThis is the truth,ЋЇ yet the disbelievers are ЋєentrenchedЋЇ in arrogance and opposition"
  38,3,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many peoples We destroyed before them, and they cried out when it was too late to escape"
  38,4,"Now, the pagans are astonished that a warner has come to them from among themselves.¬†And the disbelievers say, вАЬThis is a magician, a total liar"
  38,5,"Has he reduced ЋєallЋЇ the gods to One God? Indeed, this is something totally astonishing.вАЭ"
  38,6,"The chiefs among them went forth saying, вАЬCarry on, and stand firm in devotion to your gods. Certainly this is just a scheme Ћєfor powerЋЇ"
  38,7,We have never heard of this in the previous faith.¬†This is nothing but a fabrication
  38,8,"Has the Reminder been revealed ЋєonlyЋЇ to him out of Ћєall ofЋЇ us?вАЭ In fact, they are ЋєonlyЋЇ in doubt of My ЋєrevealedЋЇ Reminder.¬†In fact, Ћєthey do so becauseЋЇ they have not yet tasted My punishment"
  38,9,"Or Ћєis it becauseЋЇ they possess the treasuries of the mercy of your LordвАФthe Almighty, the Giver Ћєof all bountiesЋЇ"
  38,10,"Or Ћєis it becauseЋЇ the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between belongs to them? Let them then climb their way Ћєto heaven, if their claim is trueЋЇ"
  38,11,This is just another ЋєenemyЋЇ force bound for defeat out there
  38,12,"Before them, the people of Noah denied Ћєthe truthЋЇ, as did вАЩ√Вd, Pharaoh of the mighty structures"
  38,13,"Tham√їd, the people of Lot, and the residents of the Forest.¬†These were ЋєallЋЇ enemy forces"
  38,14,"Each rejected their messenger, so My punishment was justified"
  38,15,These ЋєpagansЋЇ are awaiting nothing but a single Blast that cannot be stopped
  38,16,"They say ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬOur Lord! Hasten for us our share Ћєof the punishmentЋЇ before the Day of Reckoning.вАЭ"
  38,17,"Be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ with what they say. And remember Our servant, David, the man of strength. Indeed, he ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto GodЋЇ"
  38,18,We truly subjected the mountains to hymn ЋєOur praisesЋЇ along with him in the evening and after sunrise
  38,19,"And ЋєWe subjectedЋЇ the birds, flocking together. All turned to him Ћєechoing his hymnsЋЇ"
  38,20,"We strengthened his kingship, and gave him wisdom and sound judgment"
  38,21,"Has the story of the two plaintiffs, who scaled the Ћєwall of DavidвАЩsЋЇ sanctuary, reached you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ"
  38,22,"When they came into DavidвАЩs presence, he was startled by them. They said, вАЬHave no fear. ЋєWe are merelyЋЇ two in a dispute: one of us has wronged the other. So judge between us with truthвАФdo not go beyond ЋєitЋЇвАФand guide us to the right way"
  38,23,"This is my brother.¬†He has ninety-nine sheep while I have ЋєonlyЋЇ one. ЋєStillЋЇ he asked me to give it up to him, overwhelming me with ЋєhisЋЇ argument.вАЭ"
  38,24,"David ЋєeventuallyЋЇ ruled, вАЬHe has definitely wronged you in demanding Ћєto addЋЇ your sheep to his. And certainly many partners wrong each other, except those who believe and do goodвАФbut how few are they!вАЭ Then David realized that We had tested him so he asked for his LordвАЩs forgiveness, fell down in prostration, and turned Ћєto Him in repentanceЋЇ"
  38,25,So We forgave that for him. And he will indeed have Ћєa status ofЋЇ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,26,"ЋєWe instructed him:ЋЇ вАЬO David! We have surely made you an authority in the land, so judge between people with truth. And do not follow ЋєyourЋЇ desires or they will lead you astray from GodвАЩs Way. Surely those who go astray from GodвАЩs Way will suffer a severe punishment for neglecting the Day of Reckoning.вАЭ"
  38,27,We have not created the heavens and earth and everything in between without purposeвАФas the disbelievers think. So woe to the disbelievers because of the Fire
  38,28,Or should We treat those who believe and do good like those who make mischief throughout the land? Or should We treat the righteous like the wicked
  38,29,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a blessed Book which We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ so that they may contemplate its verses, and people of reason may be mindful"
  38,30,"And We blessed David with SolomonвАФwhat an excellent servant Ћєhe wasЋЇ! Indeed, he ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto GodЋЇ"
  38,31,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the well-trained, swift horses were paraded before him in the evening"
  38,32,"He then proclaimed, вАЬI am truly in love with ЋєtheseЋЇ fine things out of remembrance for God,вАЭ until they went out of sight"
  38,33,"ЋєHe ordered,ЋЇ вАЬBring them back to me!вАЭ Then he began to rub down their legs and necks"
  38,34,"And indeed, We tested Solomon, placing a ЋєdeformedЋЇ body on his throne,¬†then he turned Ћєto God in repentanceЋЇ"
  38,35,"He prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Forgive me, and grant me an authority that will never be matched by anyone after me. You are indeed the Giver Ћєof all bountiesЋЇ.вАЭ"
  38,36,"So We subjected to him the wind, blowing gently at his command to wherever he pleased"
  38,37,And ЋєWe subjected to himЋЇ every builder and diver¬†of the jinn
  38,38,and others bound together in chains
  38,39,"ЋєGod said,ЋЇ вАЬThis is Our gift, so give or withhold Ћєas you wishЋЇ, never to be called to account.вАЭ"
  38,40,And he will indeed have Ћєa status ofЋЇ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,41,"And remember Our servant Job, when he cried out to his Lord, вАЬSatan has afflicted me with distress and suffering.вАЭ"
  38,42,"ЋєWe responded,ЋЇ вАЬStomp your foot: ЋєnowЋЇ here is a cool Ћєand refreshingЋЇ spring for washing and drinking.вАЭ"
  38,43,"And We gave him back his family, twice as many, as a mercy from Us and a lesson for people of reason"
  38,44,"ЋєAnd We said to him,ЋЇ вАЬTake in your hand a bundle of grass, and strike Ћєyour wifeЋЇ with it, and do not break your oath.вАЭ¬†We truly found him patient. What an excellent servant Ћєhe wasЋЇ! Indeed, he ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto GodЋЇ"
  38,45,"And remember Our servants: Abraham, Isaac, and JacobвАФthe men of strength and insight"
  38,46,We truly chose them for the honour of proclaiming the Hereafter
  38,47,And in Our sight they are truly among the chosen and the finest
  38,48,"Also remember Ishmael, Elisha, and в±Ђul-Kifl.¬†All are among the best"
  38,49,This is ЋєallЋЇ a reminder. And the righteous will certainly have an honourable destination
  38,50,"the Gardens of Eternity, whose gates will be open for them"
  38,51,"There they will recline, calling for abundant fruit and drink"
  38,52,And with them will be maidens of modest gaze and equal age
  38,53,This is what you are promised for the Day of Reckoning
  38,54,This is indeed Our provision that will never end
  38,55,That is that. And the transgressors will certainly have the worst destination
  38,56,"Hell, where they will burn. What an evil place to rest"
  38,57,"Let them then taste this: boiling water and ЋєoozingЋЇ pus"
  38,58,and other torments of the same sort
  38,59,"ЋєThe misleaders will say to one another,ЋЇ вАЬHere is a crowd Ћєof followersЋЇ being thrown in with us. They are not welcome, ЋєforЋЇ they ЋєtooЋЇ will burn in the Fire.вАЭ"
  38,60,"The followers will respond, вАЬNo! You are not welcome! You brought this upon us. What an evil place for settlement!вАЭ"
  38,61,"Adding, вАЬOur Lord! Whoever brought this upon us, double their punishment in the Fire.вАЭ"
  38,62,"The tyrants will ask Ћєone anotherЋЇ, вАЬBut why do we not see those we considered to be lowly"
  38,63,Were we wrong in mocking them Ћєin the worldЋЇ?¬†Or do our eyes ЋєjustЋЇ fail to see them Ћєin the FireЋЇ?вАЭ
  38,64,This dispute between the residents of the Fire will certainly come to pass
  38,65,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI am only a warner. And there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except GodвАФthe One, the Supreme"
  38,66,"ЋєHe is theЋЇ Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in betweenвАФthe Almighty, Most Forgiving.вАЭ"
  38,67,"Say, вАЬThis ЋєQuranЋЇ is momentous news"
  38,68,from which you ЋєpagansЋЇ are turning away.вАЭ
  38,69,"ЋєAnd say,ЋЇ вАЬI had no knowledge of the highest assembly Ћєin heavenЋЇ when they differed Ћєconcerning AdamЋЇ"
  38,70,What is revealed to me is that I am only sent with a clear warning.вАЭ
  38,71,"ЋєRemember, O ProphetЋЇ when your Lord said to the angels, вАЬI am going to create a human being from clay"
  38,72,"So when I have fashioned him and had a spirit of My Own ЋєcreationЋЇ breathed into him, fall down in prostration to him.вАЭ"
  38,73,So the angels prostrated all togetherвАФ
  38,74,"but not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who acted arrogantly,¬†becoming unfaithful"
  38,75,"God asked, вАЬO Ibl√Ѓs! What prevented you from prostrating to what I created with My Own Hands? Did you ЋєjustЋЇ become proud? Or have you always been arrogant?вАЭ"
  38,76,"He replied, вАЬI am better than he is: You created me from fire and him from clay.вАЭ"
  38,77,"God commanded, вАЬThen get out of Paradise, for you are truly cursed"
  38,78,And surely upon you is My condemnation until the Day of Judgment.вАЭ
  38,79,"Satan appealed, вАЬMy Lord! Then delay my end until the Day of their resurrection.вАЭ"
  38,80,"God said, вАЬYou will be delayed"
  38,81,until the appointed Day.вАЭ
  38,82,"Satan said, вАЬBy Your Glory! I will certainly mislead them all"
  38,83,except Your chosen servants among them.вАЭ
  38,84,"God concluded, вАЬThe truth isвАФand I ЋєonlyЋЇ say the truthвАФ"
  38,85,"I will surely fill up Hell with you and whoever follows you from among them, all together.вАЭ"
  38,86,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєQuranЋЇ, nor do I pretend to be someone I am not"
  38,87,It is only a reminder to the whole world
  38,88,And you will certainly know its truth before long.вАЭ
  39,1,"The revelation of this Book is from GodвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  39,2,"Indeed, We have sent down the Book to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in truth, so worship God ЋєaloneЋЇ, being sincerely devoted to Him"
  39,3,"Indeed, sincere devotion is due ЋєonlyЋЇ to God. As for those who take other lords besides Him, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬWe worship them only so they may bring us closer to God,вАЭ surely God will judge between all¬†regarding what they differed about. God certainly does not guide whoever persists in lying and disbelief"
  39,4,"Had it been GodвАЩs Will to have offspring, He could have chosen whatever He willed of His creation. Glory be to Him! He is GodвАФthe One, the Supreme"
  39,5,"He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. He wraps the night around the day, and wraps the day around the night. And He has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term. He is truly the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  39,6,"He created you ЋєallЋЇ from a single soul,¬†then from it He made its mate.¬†And He produced for you four pairs of cattle.¬†He creates you in the wombs of your mothers Ћєin stagesЋЇ, one development after another, in three layers of darkness.¬†That is GodвАФyour Lord! All authority belongs to Him. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. How can you then be turned away"
  39,7,"If you disbelieve, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ God is truly not in need of you, nor does He approve of disbelief from His servants. But if you become grateful Ћєthrough faithЋЇ, He will appreciate that from you. No soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another. Then to your Lord is your return, and He will inform you of what you used to do. He certainly knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  39,8,"When one is touched with hardship, they cry out to their Lord, turning to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. But as soon as He showers them with blessings from Him, they ЋєtotallyЋЇ forget the One they had cried to earlier, and set up equals to God to mislead ЋєothersЋЇ from His Way. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬEnjoy your disbelief for a little while! You will certainly be one of the inmates of the Fire.вАЭ"
  39,9,"ЋєAre they betterЋЇ or those who worship Ћєtheir LordЋЇ devoutly in the hours of the night, prostrating and standing, fearing the Hereafter and hoping for the mercy of their Lord? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAre those who know equal to those who do not know?вАЭ None will be mindful Ћєof thisЋЇ except people of reason"
  39,10,"Say ЋєO Prophet, that God saysЋЇ, вАЬO My servants who believe! Be mindful of your Lord. Those who do good in this world will have a good reward. And GodвАЩs earth is spacious. Only those who endure patiently will be given their reward without limit.вАЭ"
  39,11,"Say, вАЬI am commanded to worship God, being sincerely devoted to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  39,12,And I am commanded to be the first of those who submit Ћєto His WillЋЇ.вАЭ
  39,13,"Say, вАЬI truly fearвАФif I were to disobey my LordвАФthe torment of a tremendous Day.вАЭ"
  39,14,"Say, вАЬIt is ЋєonlyЋЇ God that I worship, being sincere in my devotion to Him"
  39,15,"Worship then whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ you want instead of Him.вАЭ Say, вАЬThe ЋєtrueЋЇ losers are those who will lose themselves and their families on Judgment Day. That is indeed the clearest loss.вАЭ"
  39,16,"They will have layers of fire above and below them. That is what God warns His servants with. So fear Me, O My servants"
  39,17,"And those who shun the worship of false gods, turning to God ЋєaloneЋЇ, will have good news. So give good news to My servants ЋєO ProphetЋЇвАФ"
  39,18,"those who listen to what is said and follow the best of it.¬†These are the ones ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided by God, and these are ЋєtrulyЋЇ the people of reason"
  39,19,What about those against whom the decree of torment has been justified? Is it you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who will then save those bound for the Fire
  39,20,"But those mindful of their Lord will have ЋєelevatedЋЇ mansions, built one above the other, under which rivers flow. ЋєThat isЋЇ the promise of God. ЋєAndЋЇ God never fails in ЋєHisЋЇ promise"
  39,21,"Do you not see that God sends down rain from the skyвАФchannelling it through streams in the earthвАФthen produces with it crops of various colours, then they dry up and you see them wither, and then He reduces them to chaff? Surely in this is a reminder for people of reason"
  39,22,"Can Ћєthe misguided be likeЋЇ those whose hearts God has opened to Islam, so they are enlightened by their Lord? So woe to those whose hearts are hardened at the remembrance of God! It is they who are clearly astray"
  39,23,"ЋєIt isЋЇ God ЋєWhoЋЇ has sent down the best messageвАФa Book of perfect consistency and repeated lessonsвАФwhich causes the skin Ћєand heartsЋЇ of those who fear their Lord to tremble, then their skin and hearts soften at the mention of Ћєthe mercy ofЋЇ God. That is the guidance of God, through which He guides whoever He wills. But whoever God leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  39,24,"Are those who will only have their ЋєbareЋЇ faces to shield themselves from the awful torment on Judgment Day Ћєbetter than those in ParadiseЋЇ? It will ЋєthenЋЇ be said to the wrongdoers: вАЬReap what you sowed!вАЭ"
  39,25,"Those before them ЋєalsoЋЇ rejected Ћєthe truthЋЇ, then the torment came upon them from where they least expected"
  39,26,"So God made them taste humiliation in this worldly life, but far worse is the punishment of the Hereafter, if only they knew"
  39,27,"We have certainly set forth every Ћєkind ofЋЇ lesson for people in this Quran, so perhaps they will be mindful"
  39,28,"ЋєIt isЋЇ a Quran ЋєrevealedЋЇ in Arabic without any crookedness, so perhaps they will be conscious Ћєof GodЋЇ"
  39,29,"God sets forth the parable of a slave owned by several quarrelsome masters, and a slave owned by only one master. Are they equal in condition?¬†Praise be to God! In fact, most of them do not know"
  39,30,"You ЋєO ProphetЋЇ will certainly die, and they will die too"
  39,31,Then on the Day of Judgment you will Ћєall settle yourЋЇ dispute before your Lord
  39,32,Who then does more wrong than those who lie about God and reject the truth after it has reached them? Is Hell not a ЋєfittingЋЇ home for the disbelievers
  39,33,And the one who has brought the truth and those who embrace itвАФit is they who are the righteous
  39,34,They will have whatever they desire with their Lord. That is the reward of the good-doers
  39,35,"As such, God will absolve them of ЋєevenЋЇ the worst of what they did and reward them according to the best of what they used to do"
  39,36,Is God not sufficient for His servant? Yet they threaten you with other ЋєpowerlessЋЇ gods besides Him! Whoever God leaves to stray will be left with no guide
  39,37,"And whoever God guides, none can lead astray. Is God not Almighty, capable of punishment"
  39,38,"If you ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who created the heavens and the earth, they will certainly say, вАЬGod!вАЭ Ask ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬConsider then whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you invoke besides God: if it was GodвАЩs Will to harm me, could they undo that harm? Or if He willed ЋєsomeЋЇ mercy for me, could they withhold His mercy?вАЭ Say, вАЬGod is sufficient for me. In Him ЋєaloneЋЇ the faithful put their trust.вАЭ"
  39,39,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO my people! Persist in your ways, for I ЋєtooЋЇ will persist in mine. You will soon come to know"
  39,40,who will be visited by a humiliating torment Ћєin this lifeЋЇ and overwhelmed by an everlasting punishment Ћєin the nextЋЇ.вАЭ
  39,41,"Surely We have revealed to you the Book ЋєO ProphetЋЇ with the truth for humanity. So whoever chooses to be guided, it is for their own good. And whoever chooses to stray, it is only to their own loss. You are not a keeper over them"
  39,42,"ЋєIt isЋЇ God ЋєWhoЋЇ calls back the souls Ћєof peopleЋЇ upon their death as well as Ћєthe soulsЋЇ of the living during their sleep. Then He keeps those for whom He has ordained death, and releases the others until ЋєtheirЋЇ appointed time. Surely in this are signs for people who reflect"
  39,43,"Or have they taken others besides God as intercessors? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬЋєWould they do so,ЋЇ even though those ЋєidolsЋЇ have neither authority nor intelligence?вАЭ"
  39,44,"Say, вАЬAll intercession belongs to God ЋєaloneЋЇ. To Him belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. Then to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned.вАЭ"
  39,45,"Yet when God alone is mentioned, the hearts of those who disbelieve in the Hereafter are filled with disgust. But as soon as those ЋєgodsЋЇ other than Him are mentioned, they are filled with joy"
  39,46,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO GodвАФOriginator of the heavens and the earth, Knower of the seen and unseen! You will judge between Your servants regarding their differences.вАЭ"
  39,47,"Even if the wrongdoers were to possess everything in the world twice over, they would certainly offer it to ransom themselves from the horrible punishment on Judgment Day, for they will see from God what they had never expected"
  39,48,"And the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of their deeds will unfold before them, and they will be overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  39,49,"When one is touched with hardship, they cry out to Us ЋєaloneЋЇ. Then when We shower Our blessings upon them, they say, вАЬI have been granted all this only because of ЋєmyЋЇ knowledge.вАЭ Not at all! It is Ћєno more thanЋЇ a test. But most of them do not know"
  39,50,"The same had already been said by those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them,¬†but their ЋєworldlyЋЇ gains were of no benefit to them"
  39,51,So the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of their deeds overtook them. And the wrongdoers among these ЋєpagansЋЇ will be overtaken by the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of their deeds. And they will have no escape
  39,52,Do they not know that God gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills? Surely in this are signs for people who believe
  39,53,"Say, ЋєO Prophet, that God says,ЋЇ вАЬO My servants who have exceeded the limits against their souls! Do not lose hope in GodвАЩs mercy, for God certainly forgives all sins.¬†He is indeed the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  39,54,"Turn to your Lord Ћєin repentanceЋЇ, and ЋєfullyЋЇ submit to Him before the punishment reaches you, ЋєforЋЇ then you will not be helped"
  39,55,"Follow Ћєthe Quran,ЋЇ the best of what has been revealed to you from your Lord, before the punishment takes you by surprise while you are unaware"
  39,56,"so that no ЋєsinfulЋЇ soul will say Ћєon Judgment DayЋЇ, вАШWoe to me for neglecting Ћєmy duties towardsЋЇ God, while ridiculing Ћєthe truthЋЇ.вАЩ"
  39,57,"Or Ћєa soul willЋЇ say, вАШIf only God had guided me, I would have certainly been one of the righteous.вАЩ"
  39,58,"Or say, upon seeing the torment, вАШIf only I had a second chance, I would have been one of the good-doers.вАЩ"
  39,59,"Not at all! My revelations had already come to you, but you rejected them, acted arrogantly, and were one of the disbelievers.вАЭ"
  39,60,On the Day of Judgment you will see those who lied about God with their faces gloomy. Is Hell not a ЋєfittingЋЇ home for the arrogant
  39,61,"And God will deliver those who were mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ to their place of ЋєultimateЋЇ triumph. No evil will touch them, nor will they grieve"
  39,62,"God is the Creator of all things, and He is the Maintainer of everything"
  39,63,"To Him belong the keys Ћєof the treasuriesЋЇ¬†of the heavens and the earth. As for those who rejected the signs of God, it is they who will be the ЋєtrueЋЇ losers"
  39,64,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAre you urging me to worship ЋєanyoneЋЇ other than God, O ignorant ones?вАЭ"
  39,65,"It has already been revealed to youвАФand to those ЋєprophetsЋЇ before youвАФthat if you associate others Ћєwith GodЋЇ, your deeds will certainly be void and you will truly be one of the losers"
  39,66,"Rather, worship God ЋєaloneЋЇ and be one of the grateful"
  39,67,"They have not shown God His proper reverenceвАФwhen on the Day of Judgment the ЋєwholeЋЇ earth will be in His Grip, and the heavens will be rolled up in His Right Hand. Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ"
  39,68,"The Trumpet will be blown and all those in the heavens and all those on the earth will fall dead, except those God wills Ћєto spareЋЇ. Then it will be blown again and they will rise up at once, looking on Ћєin anticipationЋЇ"
  39,69,"The earth¬†will shine with the light of its Lord, the record Ћєof deedsЋЇ will be laid ЋєopenЋЇ, the prophets and the witnesses will be brought forwardвАФand judgment will be passed on all with fairness. None will be wronged"
  39,70,"Every soul will be paid in full for its deeds, for God knows best what they have done"
  39,71,"Those who disbelieved will be driven to Hell in ЋєsuccessiveЋЇ groups. When they arrive there, its gates will be opened and its keepers will ask them: вАЬDid messengers not come to you from among yourselves, reciting to you the revelations of your Lord and warning you of the coming of this Day of yours?вАЭ The disbelievers will cry, вАЬYes ЋєindeedЋЇ! But the decree of torment has come to pass against the disbelievers.вАЭ"
  39,72,"It will be said to them, вАЬEnter the gates of Hell, to stay there forever.вАЭ What an evil home for the arrogant"
  39,73,"And those who were mindful of their Lord will be led to Paradise in ЋєsuccessiveЋЇ groups. When they arrive at its ЋєalreadyЋЇ open gates, its keepers will say, вАЬPeace be upon you! You have done well, so come in, to stay forever.вАЭ"
  39,74,"The righteous will say, вАЬPraise be to God Who has fulfilled His promise to us, and made us inherit the ЋєeverlastingЋЇ land¬†to settle in Paradise wherever we please.вАЭ How excellent is the reward of those who work ЋєrighteousnessЋЇ"
  39,75,"You will see the angels all around the Throne, glorifying the praises of their Lord, for judgment will have been passed on all with fairness. And it will be said,¬†вАЬPraise be to GodвАФLord of all worlds!вАЭ"
  40,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  40,2,"The revelation of this Book is from GodвАФthe Almighty, All-Knowing"
  40,3,"the Forgiver of sin and Accepter of repentance, the Severe in punishment, and Infinite in bounty. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. To Him ЋєaloneЋЇ is the final return"
  40,4,"None disputes the signs of God except the disbelievers, so do not be deceived by their prosperity throughout the land"
  40,5,"Before them, the people of Noah denied Ћєthe truthЋЇ, as did ЋєotherЋЇ enemy forces afterwards. Every community plotted against its prophet to seize him, and argued in falsehood, ЋєhopingЋЇ to discredit the truth with it. So I seized them. And how ЋєhorribleЋЇ was My punishment"
  40,6,And so your LordвАЩs decree has been proven true against the disbelieversвАФthat they will be the inmates of the Fire
  40,7,"Those ЋєangelsЋЇ who carry the Throne and those around it glorify the praises of their Lord, have faith in Him, and seek forgiveness for the believers, Ћєpraying:ЋЇ вАЬOur Lord! You encompass everything in ЋєYourЋЇ mercy and knowledge. So forgive those who repent and follow Your Way, and protect them from the torment of the Hellfire"
  40,8,"Our Lord! Admit them into the Gardens of Eternity which You have promised them, along with the righteous among their parents, spouses, and descendants. You ЋєaloneЋЇ are truly the Almighty, All-Wise"
  40,9,And protect them from Ћєthe consequences of theirЋЇ evil deeds. For whoever You protect from the evil of their deeds on that Day will have been shown Your mercy. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the ultimate triumph.вАЭ
  40,10,"Indeed, it will be announced to the disbelievers, вАЬGodвАЩs contempt for youвАФas you disbelieved when invited to beliefвАФwas far worse than your contempt for one another ЋєTodayЋЇ.вАЭ"
  40,11,"They will plead, вАЬOur Lord! You made us lifeless twice, and gave us life twice.¬†Now we confess our sins. So is there any way out?вАЭ"
  40,12,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬЋєNo!ЋЇ This is because when God alone was invoked, you ЋєstaunchlyЋЇ disbelieved. But when others were associated with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ, you ЋєreadilyЋЇ believed. So ЋєTodayЋЇ judgment belongs to God ЋєaloneЋЇвАФthe Most High, All-Great.вАЭ"
  40,13,He is the One Who shows you His signs and sends down Ћєrain asЋЇ a provision for you from the sky. ЋєButЋЇ none will be mindful except those who turn Ћєto HimЋЇ
  40,14,"So call upon God with sincere devotion, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  40,15,"ЋєHe isЋЇ Highly Exalted in rank, Lord of the Throne. He sends down the revelation by His command to whoever He wills of His servants to warn ЋєallЋЇ of the Day of MeetingвАФ"
  40,16,"the Day all will appear Ћєbefore GodЋЇ. Nothing about them will be hidden from Him. ЋєHe will ask,ЋЇ вАЬWho does all authority belong to this Day? To GodвАФthe One, the Supreme"
  40,17,Today every soul will be rewarded for what it has done. No injustice Today! Surely God is swift in reckoning.вАЭ
  40,18,"Warn them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ of the approaching Day when the hearts will jump into the throats, suppressing distress. The wrongdoers will have neither a close friend nor intercessor to be heard"
  40,19,God ЋєevenЋЇ knows the sly glances of the eyes and whatever the hearts conceal
  40,20,"And God judges with the truth, while those ЋєidolsЋЇ they invoke besides Him cannot judge at all. Indeed, God ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  40,21,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them? They were far superior in might and Ћєricher inЋЇ monuments throughout the land. But God seized them for their sins, and they had no protector from God"
  40,22,"That was because their messengers used to come to them with clear proofs, but they persisted in disbelief. So God seized them. Surely He is All-Powerful, severe in punishment"
  40,23,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs and compelling proof"
  40,24,"to Pharaoh, Ham√Ґn, and Korah. But they responded: вАЬMagician! Total liar!вАЭ"
  40,25,"Then, when he came to them with the truth from Us, they said, вАЬKill the sons of those who believe with him and keep their women.вАЭ But the plotting of the disbelievers was only in vain"
  40,26,"And Pharaoh said, вАЬLet me kill Moses, and let him call upon his Lord! I truly fear that he may change your traditions or cause mischief in the land.вАЭ"
  40,27,"Moses replied, вАЬI seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every arrogant person who does not believe in the Day of Reckoning.вАЭ"
  40,28,"A believing man from PharaohвАЩs people, who was hiding his faith, argued, вАЬWill you kill a man¬†ЋєonlyЋЇ for saying: вАШMy Lord is God,вАЩ while he has in fact come to you with clear proofs from your Lord? If he is a liar, it will be to his own loss. But if he is truthful, then you will be afflicted with some of what he is threatening you with. Surely God does not guide whoever is a transgressor, a total liar"
  40,29,"O my people! Authority belongs to you today, reigning supreme in the land. But who would help us against the torment of God, if it were to befall us?вАЭ Pharaoh assured Ћєhis peopleЋЇ, вАЬI am telling you only what I believe, and I am leading you only to the way of guidance.вАЭ"
  40,30,"And the man who believed cautioned, вАЬO my people! I truly fear for you the doom of ЋєearlierЋЇ enemy forcesвАФ"
  40,31,"like the fate of the people of Noah, вАЩ»Вd, Tham√їd, and those after them. For God would never will to wrong ЋєHisЋЇ servants"
  40,32,O my people! I truly fear for you the Day all will be crying out Ћєto each otherЋЇвАФ
  40,33,"the Day you will Ћєtry in vain toЋЇ turn your backs and run away, with no one to protect you from God. And whoever God leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  40,34,"Joseph already came to you¬†earlier with clear proofs, yet you never ceased to doubt what he came to you with. When he died you said, вАШGod will never send a messenger after him.вАЩ This is how God leaves every transgressor and doubter to strayвАФ"
  40,35,those who dispute GodвАЩs signs with no proof given to them. How despicable is that for God and the believers! This is how God seals the heart of every arrogant tyrant.вАЭ
  40,36,"Pharaoh ordered, вАЬO Ham√Ґn! Build me a high tower so I may reach the pathways"
  40,37,"leading up to the heavens and look for the God of Moses, although I am sure he is a liar.вАЭ¬†And so PharaohвАЩs evil deeds were made so appealing to him that he was hindered from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way. But the plotting of Pharaoh was only in vain"
  40,38,"And the man who believed urged, вАЬO my people! Follow me, ЋєandЋЇ I will lead you to the Way of Guidance"
  40,39,"O my people! This worldly life is only Ћєa fleetingЋЇ enjoyment, whereas the Hereafter is truly the home of settlement"
  40,40,"Whoever does an evil deed will only be paid back with its equivalent. And whoever does good, whether male or female, and is a believer, they will enter Paradise, where they will be provided for without limit"
  40,41,"O my people! How is it that I invite you to salvation, while you invite me to the Fire"
  40,42,"You invite me to disbelieve in God and associate with Him what I have no knowledge of, while I invite you to the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  40,43,"There is no doubt that whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you invite me to ЋєworshipЋЇ are not worthy to be invoked either in this world or the Hereafter.¬†ЋєUndoubtedly,ЋЇ our return is to God, and the transgressors will be the inmates of the Fire"
  40,44,"You will remember what I say to you, and I entrust my affairs to God. Surely God is All-Seeing of all ЋєHisЋЇ servants.вАЭ"
  40,45,So God protected him from the evil of their schemes. And PharaohвАЩs people were overwhelmed by an evil punishment
  40,46,"they are exposed to the Fire Ћєin their gravesЋЇ morning and evening. And on the Day the Hour will be established Ћєit will be saidЋЇ, вАЬAdmit PharaohвАЩs people into the harshest punishment Ћєof HellЋЇ.вАЭ"
  40,47,"ЋєConsider the DayЋЇ when they will dispute in the Fire, and the lowly ЋєfollowersЋЇ will appeal to the arrogant ЋєleadersЋЇ, вАЬWe were your ЋєdedicatedЋЇ followers, will you then shield us from a portion of the Fire?вАЭ"
  40,48,"The arrogant will say, вАЬWe are all in it! ЋєForЋЇ God has already passed judgment over ЋєHisЋЇ servants.вАЭ"
  40,49,"And those in the Fire will cry out to the keepers of Hell,¬†вАЬPray to your Lord to lighten the torment for us ЋєevenЋЇ for one day!вАЭ"
  40,50,"The keepers will reply, вАЬDid your messengers not ЋєconstantlyЋЇ come to you with clear proofs?вАЭ They will say, вАЬYes Ћєthey didЋЇ.вАЭ The keepers will say, вАЬThen pray! Though the prayer of the disbelievers is only in vain.вАЭ"
  40,51,"We certainly help Our messengers and the believers, ЋєbothЋЇ in this worldly life and on the Day the witnesses will stand forth Ћєfor testimonyЋЇвАФ"
  40,52,"the Day the wrongdoersвАЩ excuses will be of no benefit to them. They will be condemned, and will have the worst outcome"
  40,53,"And indeed, We gave Moses ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance, and made the Children of Israel inherit the ScriptureвАФ"
  40,54,a guide and a reminder to people of reason
  40,55,"So be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, ЋєforЋЇ GodвАЩs promise is certainly true. Seek forgiveness for your shortcomings.¬†And glorify the praises of your Lord morning and evening"
  40,56,"Surely those who dispute GodвАЩs signsвАФwith no proof given to themвАФhave nothing in their hearts but greed for dominance, which they will never attain. So seek refuge in God. Indeed, He alone is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  40,57,"The creation of the heavens and the earth is certainly greater than the re-creation of humankind, but most people do not know"
  40,58,"Those blind Ћєto the truthЋЇ and those who can see are not equal, nor are those who believe and do good ЋєequalЋЇ to those who do evil. Yet you are hardly mindful"
  40,59,"The Hour is certainly coming, there is no doubt about it. But most people do not believe"
  40,60,"Your Lord has proclaimed, вАЬCall upon Me, I will respond to you. Surely those who are too proud to worship Me will enter Hell, fully humbled.вАЭ"
  40,61,"It is God Who has made the night for you to rest in and the day bright. Surely God is ever Bountiful to humanity, but most people are ungrateful"
  40,62,"That is God, your Lord, the Creator of all things. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. How can you then be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  40,63,This is how those who used to reject GodвАЩs signs were ЋєalsoЋЇ deluded
  40,64,"It is God Who made the earth a place of settlement for you and the sky a canopy. He shaped you Ћєin the wombЋЇ, perfecting your form. And He has provided you with what is good and lawful. That is GodвАФyour Lord. So Blessed is God, Lord of all worlds"
  40,65,"He is the Ever-Living. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. So call upon Him with sincere devotion, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬAll praise is for GodвАФLord of all worlds.вАЭ"
  40,66,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI have been forbidden to worship those ЋєidolsЋЇ you worship besides God, since clear proofs have come to me from my Lord. And I have been commanded to ЋєfullyЋЇ submit to the Lord of all worlds.вАЭ"
  40,67,"He is the One Who created you¬†from dust, then from a sperm-drop,¬†then Ћєdeveloped you intoЋЇ a clinging clot Ћєof bloodЋЇ,¬†then He brings you forth as infants, so that you may reach your prime, and become oldвАФthough some of you ЋєmayЋЇ die soonerвАФreaching an appointed time, so perhaps you may understand ЋєGodвАЩs powerЋЇ"
  40,68,"He is the One Who gives life and causes death. When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, вАЬBe!вАЭ And it is"
  40,69,Have you not seen how those who dispute GodвАЩs signs are turned away
  40,70,ЋєThey areЋЇ the ones who reject this Book and all ЋєscripturesЋЇ We sent Our messengers with. So they will know Ћєthe consequencesЋЇ
  40,71,when shackles will be around their necks and chains Ћєon their legsЋЇ. They will be dragged
  40,72,"through boiling water, then burned in the Fire Ћєas fuelЋЇ"
  40,73,"Then they will be asked, вАЬWhere are those ЋєidolsЋЇ you used to associate"
  40,74,"with God?вАЭ They will cry, вАЬThey have ЋєallЋЇ failed us. In fact, we did not invoke anything ЋєrealЋЇ before.вАЭ This is how God leaves the disbelievers to stray"
  40,75,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬThis ЋєpunishmentЋЇ is for being prideful on earth unjustly and for acting arrogantly"
  40,76,"Enter the gates of Hell, to stay there forever. What an evil home for the arrogant!вАЭ"
  40,77,"So be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. Surely GodвАЩs promise is true. Whether We show you some of what We threaten them with, or cause you to die Ћєbefore thatЋЇ, to Us they will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  40,78,"We already sent messengers before you. We have told you the stories of some of them, while others We have not. It was not for any messenger to bring a sign without GodвАЩs permission. But when GodвАЩs decree comes, judgment will be passed with fairness, and the people of falsehood will then be in ЋєtotalЋЇ loss"
  40,79,It is God Who made cattle for you so that you may ride some and eat others
  40,80,"Also, you find in them ЋєotherЋЇ benefits.¬†And by means of them you may reach destinations you desire. And you are carried upon Ћєsome ofЋЇ them and upon ships"
  40,81,And He shows you His signs. Now which of GodвАЩs signs will you deny
  40,82,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those who were ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them? They were far superior in might and Ћєricher inЋЇ monuments throughout the land, but their ЋєworldlyЋЇ gains were of no benefit to them"
  40,83,"When their messengers came to them with clear proofs, they were prideful in whatever ЋєworldlyЋЇ knowledge they had,¬†and were ЋєultimatelyЋЇ overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  40,84,"When they saw Our punishment, they cried, вАЬЋєNowЋЇ we believe in God alone and reject what we had been associating with Him!вАЭ"
  40,85,But their faith was of no benefit to them when they saw Our torment. This has ЋєalwaysЋЇ been GodвАЩs way Ћєof dealingЋЇ with His ЋєwickedЋЇ servants. Then and there the disbelievers were in ЋєtotalЋЇ loss
  41,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  41,2,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a revelation from the Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  41,3,ЋєIt isЋЇ a Book whose verses are perfectly explainedвАФa Quran in Arabic for people who know
  41,4,"delivering good news and warning. Yet most of them turn away, so they do not hear"
  41,5,"They say, вАЬOur hearts are veiled against what you are calling us to, there is deafness in our ears, and there is a barrier between us and you. So do Ћєwhatever you wantЋЇ and so shall we!вАЭ"
  41,6,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI am only a man like you, ЋєbutЋЇ it has been revealed to me that your God is only One God. So take the Straight Way towards Him, and seek His forgiveness. And woe to the polytheistsвАФ"
  41,7,those who do not pay alms-tax and are in denial of the Hereafter
  41,8,ЋєButЋЇ those who believe and do good will certainly have a never-ending reward
  41,9,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬHow can you disbelieve in the One Who created the earth in two Days? And how can you set up equals with Him? That is the Lord of all worlds"
  41,10,"He placed on the earth firm mountains, standing high, showered His blessings upon it, and ordained ЋєallЋЇ its means of sustenanceвАФtotaling four Days exactlyвАФfor all who ask"
  41,11,"Then He turned towards the heaven when it was Ћєstill likeЋЇ smoke, saying to it and to the earth, вАШSubmit, willingly or unwillingly.вАЩ They both responded, вАШWe submit willingly.вАЩ"
  41,12,"So He formed the heaven into seven heavens in two Days, assigning to each its mandate. And We adorned the lowest heaven with Ћєstars likeЋЇ lamps Ћєfor beautyЋЇ and for protection. That is the design of the Almighty, All-Knowing.вАЭ"
  41,13,"If they turn away, then say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI warn you of a ЋєmightyЋЇ blast, like the one that befell вАЩ»Вd and Tham√їd.вАЭ"
  41,14,"The messengers had come to them from all angles, Ћєproclaiming,ЋЇ вАЬWorship none but God.вАЭ They responded, вАЬHad our Lord willed, He could have easily sent down angels ЋєinsteadЋЇ. So we totally reject what you have been sent with.вАЭ"
  41,15,"As for вАЩ»Вd, they acted arrogantly throughout the land with no right, boasting, вАЬWho is superior to us in might?вАЭ Did they not see that God ЋєHimselfЋЇ, Who created them, was far superior to them in might? Still they persisted in denying Our signs"
  41,16,"So We sent against them a furious wind,¬†for ЋєseveralЋЇ miserable days, to make them taste a humiliating punishment in this worldly life. But far more humiliating will be the punishment of the Hereafter. And they will not be helped"
  41,17,"As for Tham√їd, We showed them guidance, but they preferred blindness over guidance. So the blast of a disgracing punishment overtook them for what they used to commit"
  41,18,And We delivered those who were faithful and were mindful Ћєof GodЋЇ
  41,19,"ЋєConsiderЋЇ the Day ЋєwhenЋЇ the enemies of God will be gathered for the Fire, all driven in ranks"
  41,20,"When they reach it, their ears, eyes, and skin will testify against what they used to do"
  41,21,"They will ask their skin ЋєfuriouslyЋЇ, вАЬWhy have you testified against us?вАЭ It will say, вАЬWe have been made to speak by God, Who causes all things to speak. He Ћєis the One WhoЋЇ created you the first time, and to Him you were bound to return"
  41,22,"You did not Ћєbother toЋЇ hide yourselves from your ears, eyes, and skin to prevent them from testifying against you. Rather, you assumed that God did not know much of what you used to do"
  41,23,"It was that ЋєfalseЋЇ assumption you entertained about your Lord that has brought about your doom, so you have become losers.вАЭ"
  41,24,"Even if they endure patiently, the Fire will ЋєalwaysЋЇ be their home. And if they Ћєbeg toЋЇ appease Ћєtheir LordЋЇ, they will never be allowed to"
  41,25,"We placed at their disposal ЋєevilЋЇ associates who made their past and future ЋєmisdeedsЋЇ appealing to them.¬†ЋєSoЋЇ the fate of earlier communities of jinn and humans has been justified against them Ћєas wellЋЇ, ЋєforЋЇ they were truly losers"
  41,26,"The disbelievers advised Ћєone anotherЋЇ, вАЬDo not listen to this Quran but drown it out so that you may prevail.вАЭ"
  41,27,"So We will certainly make the disbelievers taste a severe punishment, and We will surely repay them according to the worst of their deeds"
  41,28,"That is the reward of GodвАЩs enemies: the Fire, which will be their eternal homeвАФa ЋєfittingЋЇ reward for their denial of Our revelations"
  41,29,"The disbelievers will ЋєthenЋЇ cry, вАЬOur Lord! Show us those jinn and humans who led us astray: we will put them under our feet so that they will be among the lowest Ћєin HellЋЇ.вАЭ"
  41,30,"Surely those who say, вАЬOur Lord is God,вАЭ and then remain steadfast, the angels descend upon them,¬†Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬDo not fear, nor grieve. Rather, rejoice in the good news of Paradise, which you have been promised"
  41,31,"We are your supporters in this worldly life and in the Hereafter. There you will have whatever your souls desire, and there you will have whatever you ask for"
  41,32,"an accommodation from the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful ЋєLordЋЇ.вАЭ"
  41,33,"And whose words are better than someone who calls ЋєothersЋЇ to God, does good, and says, вАЬI am truly one of those who submit.вАЭ"
  41,34,"Good and evil cannot be equal. Respond Ћєto evilЋЇ with what is best, then the one you are in a feud with will be like a close friend"
  41,35,But this cannot be attained except by those who are patient and who are truly fortunate
  41,36,"And if you are tempted by Satan, then seek refuge with God. Indeed, He ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  41,37,"Among His signs are the day and the night, the sun and the moon. Do not prostrate to the sun or the moon, but prostrate to God, Who created them ЋєallЋЇ, if you ЋєtrulyЋЇ worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  41,38,"But if the pagans are too proud, then Ћєlet them know thatЋЇ those ЋєangelsЋЇ nearest to your Lord glorify Him day and night, and never grow weary"
  41,39,"And among His signs is that you see the earth devoid of life, but as soon as We send down rain upon it, it begins to stir Ћєto lifeЋЇ and swell. Indeed, the One Who revives it can easily revive the dead. He is certainly Most Capable of everything"
  41,40,"Indeed, those who abuse Our revelations¬†are not hidden from Us. Who is better: the one who will be cast into the Fire or the one who will be secure on Judgment Day? Do whatever you want. He is certainly All-Seeing of what you do"
  41,41,"Indeed, those who deny the Reminder¬†after it has come to them Ћєare doomedЋЇ, for it is truly a mighty Book"
  41,42,"It cannot be proven false from any angle. ЋєIt isЋЇ a revelation from the ЋєOne Who isЋЇ All-Wise, Praiseworthy"
  41,43,ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ Nothing is said to you Ћєby the deniersЋЇ except what was already said to the messengers before you. Surely your Lord is Ћєthe LordЋЇ of forgiveness and painful punishment
  41,44,"Had We revealed it as a non-Arabic Quran, they would have certainly argued, вАЬIf only its verses were made clear Ћєin our languageЋЇ. What! A non-Arabic revelation for an Arab audience!вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIt is a guide and a healing to the believers. As for those who disbelieve, there is deafness in their ears and blindness to it Ћєin their heartsЋЇ. It is as if they are being called from a faraway place.вАЭ"
  41,45,"Indeed, We had given Moses the Scripture, but differences arose regarding it. Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord,¬†their differences would have been settled Ћєat onceЋЇ. They are truly in alarming doubt about it"
  41,46,"Whoever does good, it is to their own benefit. And whoever does evil, it is to their own loss. Your Lord is never unjust to ЋєHisЋЇ creation"
  41,47,"With Him ЋєaloneЋЇ is the knowledge of the Hour. No fruit comes out of its husk, nor does a female conceive or deliver without His knowledge. And ЋєconsiderЋЇ the Day He will call to them, вАЬWhere are My Ћєso-calledЋЇ associate-gods?вАЭ They will cry, вАЬWe declare before you that none of us testifies to that Ћєany longerЋЇ.вАЭ"
  41,48,Whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ they used to invoke besides God will fail them. And they will realize that they will have no escape
  41,49,"One never tires of praying for good. And if touched with evil, they become desperate and hopeless"
  41,50,"And if We let them taste a mercy from Us after being touched with adversity, they will certainly say, вАЬThis is what I deserve. I do not think the Hour will ЋєeverЋЇ come. And if in fact I am returned to my Lord, the finest reward with Him will definitely be mine.вАЭ But We will surely inform the disbelievers of what they used to do. And We will certainly make them taste a harsh torment"
  41,51,"When We show favour to someone, they turn away, acting arrogantly. And when touched with evil, they make endless prayers Ћєfor goodЋЇ"
  41,52,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬImagine if this ЋєQuranЋЇ is ЋєtrulyЋЇ from God and you deny it: who can be more astray than those who have gone too far in opposition Ћєto the truthЋЇ?вАЭ"
  41,53,We will show them Our signs in the universe and within themselves until it becomes clear to them that this ЋєQuranЋЇ is the truth. Is it not enough that your Lord is a Witness over all things
  41,54,They are truly in doubt of the meeting with their Lord! ЋєButЋЇ He is indeed Fully Aware of everything
  42,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  42,2,вАЩAƒ©n-Sƒ©n-Q√£f
  42,3,"And so you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are sent revelation, just like those before you, by GodвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  42,4,"To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And He is the Most High, the Greatest"
  42,5,"The heavens¬†nearly burst, one above the other, Ћєin awe of HimЋЇ. And the angels glorify the praises of their Lord, and seek forgiveness for those on earth. Surely God alone is the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  42,6,"As for those who take other protectors besides Him, God is Watchful over them. And you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are not a keeper over them"
  42,7,"And so We have revealed to you a Quran in Arabic, so you may warn the Mother of Cities¬†and everyone around it, and warn of the Day of GatheringвАФabout which there is no doubtвАФЋєwhenЋЇ a group will be in Paradise and another in the Blaze"
  42,8,"Had God willed, He could have easily made all ЋєhumanityЋЇ into a single community Ћєof believersЋЇ. But He admits into His mercy whoever He wills. And the wrongdoers will have no protector or helper"
  42,9,How can they take protectors besides Him? God alone is the Protector. He ЋєaloneЋЇ gives life to the dead. And He ЋєaloneЋЇ is Most Capable of everything
  42,10,"ЋєSay to the believers, O Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWhatever you may differ about, its judgment rests with God. That is GodвАФmy Lord. In Him I put my trust, and to Him I ЋєalwaysЋЇ turn.вАЭ"
  42,11,"ЋєHe isЋЇ the Originator of the heavens and the earth. He has made for you spouses from among yourselves, and ЋєmadeЋЇ mates for cattle Ћєas wellЋЇвАФmultiplying you ЋєbothЋЇ. There is nothing like Him, for He ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  42,12,"To Him belong the keys Ћєof the treasuriesЋЇ of the heavens and the earth. He gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills. Indeed, He has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  42,13,"He has ordained for you ЋєbelieversЋЇ the Way which He decreed for Noah, and what We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ and what We decreed for Abraham, Moses, and Jesus,¬†Ћєcommanding:ЋЇ вАЬUphold the faith, and make no divisions in it.вАЭ What you call the polytheists to is unbearable for them. God chooses for Himself whoever He wills, and guides to Himself whoever turns Ћєto HimЋЇ"
  42,14,"They did not split Ћєinto sectsЋЇ out of mutual envy until knowledge came to them.¬†Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord for an appointed term,¬†the matter would have certainly been settled between them Ћєat onceЋЇ. And surely those who were made to inherit the Scripture¬†after them are truly in alarming doubt about this ЋєQuranЋЇ"
  42,15,"Because of that, you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ will invite ЋєallЋЇ. Be steadfast as you are commanded, and do not follow their desires. And say, вАЬI believe in every Scripture God has revealed. And I am commanded to judge fairly among you. God is our Lord and your Lord. We will be accountable for our deeds and you for yours. There is no Ћєneed forЋЇ contention between us. God will gather us together Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ. And to Him is the final return.вАЭ"
  42,16,"As for those who dispute about God after He is ЋєalreadyЋЇ acknowledged Ћєby manyЋЇ, their argument is futile in the sight of their Lord. Upon them is wrath, and they will suffer a severe punishment"
  42,17,"It is God Who has revealed the Book with the truth and the balance Ћєof justiceЋЇ. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near"
  42,18,"Those who disbelieve in it Ћєask toЋЇ hasten it ЋєmockinglyЋЇ. But the believers are fearful of it, knowing that it is the truth. Surely those who dispute about the Hour have gone far astray"
  42,19,"God is Ever Kind to His servants. He provides ЋєabundantlyЋЇ to whoever He wills. And He is the All-Powerful, Almighty"
  42,20,"Whoever desires the harvest of the Hereafter, We will increase their harvest. And whoever desires ЋєonlyЋЇ the harvest of this world, We will give them some of it, but they will have no share in the Hereafter"
  42,21,"Or do they have associate-gods who have ordained for them some ЋєpolytheisticЋЇ beliefs, which God has not authorized? Had it not been for ЋєpriorЋЇ decree on Judgment, the matter would have certainly been settled between them Ћєat onceЋЇ. And surely the wrongdoers will suffer a painful punishment"
  42,22,"You will see the wrongdoers fearful Ћєof the punishmentЋЇ for what they committed but it will be inevitable for them, whereas those who believe and do good will be in the lush Gardens of Paradise. They will have whatever they desire from their Lord. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the greatest bounty"
  42,23,"That ЋєrewardЋЇ is the good news which God gives to His servants who believe and do good. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI do not ask you for a reward for this ЋєmessageЋЇвАФonly honour for ЋєourЋЇ kinship.вАЭ¬†Whoever earns a good deed, We will increase it in goodness for them. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Appreciative"
  42,24,"Or do they say, вАЬHe has fabricated a lie about God!вАЭ? ЋєIf you had,ЋЇ God would have sealed your heart, if He willed. And God wipes out falsehood and establishes the truth by His Words. He certainly knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  42,25,He is the One Who accepts repentance from His servants and pardons ЋєtheirЋЇ sins. And He knows whatever you do
  42,26,"He responds to those who believe and do good, and increases their reward out of His grace. As for the disbelievers, they will suffer a severe punishment"
  42,27,"Had God given abundant provisions to ЋєallЋЇ His servants, they would have certainly transgressed throughout the land. But He sends down whatever He wills in perfect measure. He is truly All-Aware, All-Seeing of His servants"
  42,28,"He is the One Who sends down rain after people have given up hope, spreading out His mercy. He is the Guardian, the Praiseworthy"
  42,29,"And among His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and all living beings He dispersed throughout both. And He is Most Capable of bringing all together whenever He wills"
  42,30,Whatever affliction befalls you is because of what your own hands have committed. And He pardons much
  42,31,"You can never escape ЋєHimЋЇ on earth, nor do you have any protector or helper besides God"
  42,32,And among His signs are the ships like mountains ЋєsailingЋЇ in the sea
  42,33,"If He wills, He can calm the wind, leaving the ships motionless on the water. Surely in this are signs for whoever is steadfast, grateful"
  42,34,Or He can wreck the ships for what the people have committedвАФthough He forgives muchвАФ
  42,35,so those who dispute about Our signs may know that they have no refuge
  42,36,Whatever ЋєpleasureЋЇ you have been given is Ћєno more than a fleetingЋЇ enjoyment of this worldly life. But what is with God is far better and more lasting for those who believe and put their trust in their Lord
  42,37,"who avoid major sins and shameful deeds, and forgive when angered"
  42,38,"who respond to their Lord, establish prayer, conduct their affairs by mutual consultation, and donate from what We have provided for them"
  42,39,and who enforce justice when wronged
  42,40,"The reward of an evil deed is its equivalent. But whoever pardons and seeks reconciliation, then their reward is with God. He certainly does not like the wrongdoers"
  42,41,There is no blame on those who enforce justice after being wronged
  42,42,Blame is only on those who wrong people and transgress in the land unjustly. It is they who will suffer a painful punishment
  42,43,And whoever endures patiently and forgivesвАФsurely this is a resolve to aspire to
  42,44,"And whoever God leaves to stray will have no guide after Him. You will see the wrongdoers, when they face the torment, pleading, вАЬIs there any way back Ћєto the worldЋЇ?вАЭ"
  42,45,"And you will see them exposed to the Fire, fully humbled out of disgrace, stealing glances Ћєat itЋЇ. And the believers will say, вАЬThe ЋєtrueЋЇ losers are those who have lost themselves and their families on Judgment Day.вАЭ The wrongdoers will certainly be in everlasting torment"
  42,46,"They will have no protectors to help them against God. And whoever God leaves to stray, for them there is no way"
  42,47,"Respond to your Lord before the coming of a Day from God that cannot be averted. There will be no refuge for you then, nor Ћєgrounds forЋЇ denial Ћєof sinsЋЇ"
  42,48,"But if they turn away, We have not sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as a keeper over them. Your duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ. And indeed, when We let someone taste a mercy from Us, they become prideful ЋєbecauseЋЇ of it. But when afflicted with evil because of what their hands have done, then one becomes totally ungrateful"
  42,49,"To God ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He creates whatever He wills. He blesses whoever He wills with daughters, and blesses whoever He wills with sons"
  42,50,"or grants both, sons and daughters, Ћєto whoever He willsЋЇ, and leaves whoever He wills infertile. He is indeed All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  42,51,"It is not ЋєpossibleЋЇ for a human being to have God communicate with them, except through inspiration, or from behind a veil, or by sending a messenger-angel to reveal whatever He wills by His permission. He is surely Most High, All-Wise"
  42,52,"And so We have sent to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ a revelation by Our command. You did not know of ЋєthisЋЇ Book and faith ЋєbeforeЋЇ. But We have made it a light, by which We guide whoever We will of Our servants. And you are truly leading ЋєallЋЇ to the Straight PathвАФ"
  42,53,"the Path of God, to Whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Surely to God all matters will return Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ"
  43,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  43,2,By the clear Book
  43,3,"Certainly, We have made it a Quran in Arabic so perhaps you will understand"
  43,4,"And indeed, it isвАФin the Master Record¬†with UsвАФhighly esteemed, rich in wisdom"
  43,5,Should We then turn the ЋєQuranicЋЇ Reminder away from you ЋєsimplyЋЇ because you have been a transgressing people
  43,6,ЋєImagineЋЇ how many prophets We sent to those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before
  43,7,But no prophet ever came to them without being mocked
  43,8,So We destroyed those who were far mightier than these ЋєMeccansЋЇ. The examples of ЋєtheirЋЇ predecessors have ЋєalreadyЋЇ been related
  43,9,"If you ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who created the heavens and the earth, they will certainly say, вАЬThe Almighty, All-Knowing did.вАЭ"
  43,10,"ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who has laid out the earth for you, and set in it pathways for you so that you may find your way"
  43,11,"And ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who sends down rain from the sky in perfect measure, with which We give life to a lifeless land. And so will you be brought forth Ћєfrom the graveЋЇ"
  43,12,"And ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who created all Ћєthings inЋЇ pairs,¬†and made for you ships and animals to ride"
  43,13,"so that you may sit firmly on their backs, and remember your LordвАЩs blessings once you are settled on them, saying, вАЬGlory be to the One Who has subjected these for us, for we could have never done so Ћєon our ownЋЇ"
  43,14,And surely to our Lord we will ЋєallЋЇ return.вАЭ
  43,15,"Still the pagans have made some of His creation out to be a part of Him.¬†Indeed, humankind is clearly ungrateful"
  43,16,"Has He taken Ћєangels as HisЋЇ daughters from what He created, and favoured you ЋєO pagansЋЇ with sons"
  43,17,"Whenever one of them is given the good news of what they attribute to the Most Compassionate,¬†his face grows gloomy, as he suppresses his rage"
  43,18,ЋєDo they attribute to HimЋЇ those who are brought up in fineries and are not commanding in disputes
  43,19,"Still they have labelled the angels, who are servants of the Most Compassionate, as female. Did they witness their creation? Their statement will be recorded, and they will be questioned"
  43,20,"And they argue, вАЬHad the Most Compassionate willed, we would have never worshipped them.вАЭ They have no knowledge Ћєin supportЋЇ of this ЋєclaimЋЇ. They do nothing but lie"
  43,21,"Or have We given them a Book Ћєfor proofЋЇ, before this ЋєQuranЋЇ, to which they are holding firm"
  43,22,"In fact, they say, вАЬWe found our forefathers following a ЋєparticularЋЇ way, and we are following in their footsteps.вАЭ"
  43,23,"Similarly, whenever We sent a warner to a society before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, its ЋєspoiledЋЇ elite would say, вАЬWe found our forefathers following a ЋєparticularЋЇ way, and we are walking in their footsteps.вАЭ"
  43,24,"Each ЋєwarnerЋЇ asked, вАЬEven if what I brought you is better guidance than what you found your forefathers practicing?вАЭ They replied, вАЬWe totally reject whatever you have been sent with.вАЭ"
  43,25,So We inflicted punishment upon them. See then what was the fate of the deniers
  43,26,"ЋєRemember, O ProphetЋЇ when Abraham declared to his father and his people, вАЬI am totally free of whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ you worship"
  43,27,"except the One Who originated me, and He will surely guide me.вАЭ"
  43,28,"And he left this enduring declaration among his descendants, so they may ЋєalwaysЋЇ turn back Ћєto GodЋЇ"
  43,29,"In fact, I had allowed enjoyment for these ЋєMeccansЋЇ and their forefathers, until the truth came to them along with a messenger making things clear"
  43,30,"ЋєButЋЇ when the truth came to them, they said, вАЬThis is magic, and we totally reject it.вАЭ"
  43,31,"And they exclaimed, вАЬIf only this Quran was revealed to a great man from Ћєone ofЋЇ the two cities!вАЭ"
  43,32,Is it they who distribute your LordвАЩs mercy? We ЋєaloneЋЇ have distributed their ЋєveryЋЇ livelihood among them in this worldly life and raised some of them in rank above others so that some may employ others in service. ЋєButЋЇ your LordвАЩs mercy is far better than whatever ЋєwealthЋЇ they amass
  43,33,"Were it not that people might Ћєbe tempted toЋЇ become one community Ћєof disbelieversЋЇ, We would have supplied the homes of ЋєonlyЋЇ those who disbelieve in the Most Compassionate with silver roofs and ЋєsilverЋЇ stairways to ascend"
  43,34,as well as ЋєsilverЋЇ gates and thrones to recline on
  43,35,and ornaments Ћєof goldЋЇ. Yet all this is no more than a ЋєfleetingЋЇ enjoyment in this worldly life. ЋєButЋЇ the Hereafter with your Lord is ЋєonlyЋЇ for those mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ
  43,36,"And whoever turns a blind eye to the Reminder of the Most Compassionate, We place at the disposal of each a devilish one as their close associate"
  43,37,who will certainly hinder them from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way while they think they are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided
  43,38,"But when such a person comes to Us, one will say Ћєto their associateЋЇ, вАЬI wish you were as distant from me as the east is from the west! What an evil associate Ћєyou wereЋЇ!вАЭ"
  43,39,"ЋєIt will be said to both,ЋЇ вАЬSince you all did wrong, sharing in the punishment will be of no benefit to you this Day.вАЭ"
  43,40,"Can you make the deaf hear, or guide the blind or those clearly astray"
  43,41,"Even if We take you away Ћєfrom this worldЋЇ, We will surely inflict punishment upon them"
  43,42,"Or if We show you what We threaten them with, We certainly have full power over them"
  43,43,So hold firmly to what has been revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. You are truly on the Straight Path
  43,44,Surely this ЋєQuranЋЇ is a glory for you and your people. And you will ЋєallЋЇ be questioned Ћєabout itЋЇ
  43,45,Ask Ћєthe followers ofЋЇ the messengers that We already sent before you if We ЋєeverЋЇ appointed ЋєotherЋЇ gods to be worshipped besides the Most Compassionate
  43,46,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs, and he said: вАЬI am a messenger of the Lord of all worlds.вАЭ"
  43,47,"But as soon as he came to them with Our signs, they laughed at them"
  43,48,"although every sign We showed them was greater than the one before.¬†Ultimately, We seized them with torments so that they might return Ћєto the Right PathЋЇ"
  43,49,"ЋєThenЋЇ they pleaded, вАЬO ЋєmightyЋЇ magician! Pray to your Lord on our behalf, by virtue of the covenant He made with you.¬†We will certainly accept guidance.вАЭ"
  43,50,"But as soon as We removed the torments from them, they broke their promise"
  43,51,"And Pharaoh called out to his people, boasting, вАЬO my people! Am I not sovereign over Egypt as well as ЋєallЋЇ these streams¬†flowing at my feet? Can you not see"
  43,52,Am I not better than this nobody who can hardly express himself
  43,53,Why then have no golden bracelets Ћєof kingshipЋЇ been granted to him or angels come with him as escorts!вАЭ
  43,54,"And so he fooled his people, and they obeyed him. They were truly a rebellious people"
  43,55,"So when they enraged Us, We inflicted punishment upon them, drowning them all"
  43,56,And We made them an example and a lesson for those after them
  43,57,"When the son of Mary was cited as an example Ћєin argumentЋЇ, your people ЋєO ProphetЋЇ broke into ЋєjoyfulЋЇ applause"
  43,58,"They exclaimed, вАЬWhich is better: our gods or Jesus?вАЭ They cite him only to argue. In fact, they are a people prone to dispute"
  43,59,"He was only a servant We showed favour to, and made as an example for the Children of Israel"
  43,60,"Had We willed, We could have easily replaced you ЋєallЋЇ with angels,¬†succeeding one another on earth"
  43,61,"And his ЋєsecondЋЇ coming is truly a sign for the Hour. So have no doubt about it, and follow me. This is the Straight Path"
  43,62,"And do not let Satan hinder you, ЋєforЋЇ he is certainly your sworn enemy"
  43,63,"When Jesus came with clear proofs, he declared, вАЬI have come to you with wisdom, and to clarify to you some of what you differ about. So fear God, and obey me"
  43,64,"Surely God ЋєaloneЋЇ is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. This is the Straight Path.вАЭ"
  43,65,"Yet their ЋєvariousЋЇ groups have differed among themselves Ћєabout himЋЇ, so woe to the wrongdoers when they face the torment of a painful Day"
  43,66,Are they waiting for the Hour to take them by surprise when they least expect ЋєitЋЇ
  43,67,"Close friends will be enemies to one another on that Day, except the righteous"
  43,68,"Ћєwho will be told,ЋЇ вАЬO My servants! There is no fear for you Today, nor will you grieveвАФ"
  43,69,ЋєthoseЋЇ who believed in Our signs and ЋєfullyЋЇ submitted Ћєto UsЋЇ
  43,70,"Enter Paradise, you and your spouses, rejoicing.вАЭ"
  43,71,Golden trays and cups will be passed around to them. There will be whatever the souls desire and the eyes delight in. And you will be there forever
  43,72,That is the Paradise which you will be awarded for what you used to do
  43,73,There you will have abundant fruit¬†to eat from
  43,74,"Indeed, the wicked will be in the torment of Hell forever"
  43,75,"It will never be lightened for them, and there they will be overwhelmed with despair"
  43,76,"We did not wrong them, but it was they who were the wrongdoers"
  43,77,"They will cry, вАЬO M√Ґlik!¬†Let your Lord finish us off.вАЭ He will answer, вАЬYou are definitely here to stay.вАЭ"
  43,78,"We certainly brought the truth to you, but most of you were resentful of the truth"
  43,79,Or have they mastered some ЋєevilЋЇ plan? Then We ЋєtooЋЇ are surely planning
  43,80,"Or do they think that We do not hear their ЋєevilЋЇ thoughts and secret talks? Yes ЋєWe doЋЇ! And Our messenger-angels are in their presence, recording Ћєit allЋЇ"
  43,81,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf the Most Compassionate ЋєreallyЋЇ had offspring, I would be the first worshipper.вАЭ"
  43,82,"Glorified is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, far above what they claim"
  43,83,"So let them indulge Ћєin falsehoodЋЇ and amuse ЋєthemselvesЋЇ until they face their Day, which they have been warned of"
  43,84,"It is He Who is Ћєthe onlyЋЇ God in the heavens and Ћєthe onlyЋЇ God on the earth. For He is the All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  43,85,And Blessed is the One to Whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between! With Him ЋєaloneЋЇ is the knowledge of the Hour. And to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned
  43,86,"ЋєButЋЇ those Ћєobjects of worshipЋЇ they invoke besides Him have no power to intercede, except those who testify to the truth knowingly"
  43,87,"If you ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who created them, they will certainly say, вАЬGod!вАЭ How can they then be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  43,88,"ЋєGod is Aware ofЋЇ the ProphetвАЩs cry: вАЬO my Lord! Indeed, these are a people who persist in disbelief.вАЭ"
  43,89,So bear with them and respond with peace. They will soon come to know
  44,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  44,2,By the clear Book
  44,3,"Indeed, We sent it down on a blessed night,¬†for We always warn Ћєagainst evilЋЇ"
  44,4,On that night every matter of wisdom is ordained
  44,5,"by a command from Us, for We have always sent ЋєmessengersЋЇ"
  44,6,"as a mercy from your Lord. He ЋєaloneЋЇ is truly the All-Hearing, All-KnowingвАФ"
  44,7,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between, if only you had sure faith"
  44,8,"There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. He ЋєaloneЋЇ gives life and causes death. ЋєHe isЋЇ your Lord, and the Lord of your forefathers"
  44,9,"In fact, they are in doubt, amusing themselves"
  44,10,"Wait then ЋєO ProphetЋЇ for the day ЋєwhenЋЇ the sky will be veiled in haze,¬†clearly visible"
  44,11,"overwhelming the people. ЋєThey will cry,ЋЇ вАЬThis is a painful torment"
  44,12,"Our Lord! Remove ЋєthisЋЇ torment from us, ЋєandЋЇ we will certainly believe.вАЭ"
  44,13,"How can they be reminded when a messenger has already come to them, making things clear"
  44,14,"then they turned away from him, saying, вАЬA madman, taught by others!вАЭ"
  44,15,"Indeed, We will remove ЋєthatЋЇ torment for a while, and you ЋєMeccansЋЇ will return Ћєto disbeliefЋЇ"
  44,16,"ЋєThenЋЇ on the Day We will deal ЋєyouЋЇ the fiercest blow, We will surely inflict punishment"
  44,17,"Indeed, before them We tested PharaohвАЩs people: a noble messenger came to them"
  44,18,"Ћєproclaiming,ЋЇ вАЬHand over the servants of God to me.¬†I am truly a trustworthy messenger to you"
  44,19,And do not be arrogant with God. I have certainly come to you with a compelling proof
  44,20,"And indeed, I seek refuge with my Lord and your Lord so you do not stone me Ћєto deathЋЇ"
  44,21,"ЋєButЋЇ if you do not believe me, then let me be.вАЭ"
  44,22,"Ultimately, he cried out to his Lord, вАЬThese are a wicked people!вАЭ"
  44,23,"ЋєGod responded,ЋЇ вАЬLeave with My servants at night, for you will surely be pursued"
  44,24,"And leave the sea parted, for they are certainly an army bound to drown.вАЭ"
  44,25,ЋєImagineЋЇ how many gardens and springs the tyrants¬†left behind
  44,26,as well as ЋєvariousЋЇ crops and splendid residences
  44,27,and luxuries which they fully enjoyed
  44,28,So it was. And We awarded it ЋєallЋЇ to another people
  44,29,"Neither heaven nor earth wept over them, nor was their fate delayed"
  44,30,And We certainly delivered the Children of Israel from the humiliating torment
  44,31,"of Pharaoh. He was truly a tyrant, a transgressor"
  44,32,"And indeed, We chose the Israelites knowingly above the others"
  44,33,And We showed them signs in which there was a clear test
  44,34,"Indeed, these ЋєMeccansЋЇ say"
  44,35,"вАЬThere is nothing beyond our first death, and we will never be resurrected"
  44,36,"Bring ЋєbackЋЇ our forefathers, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  44,37,"Are they superior to the people of TubbaвАЩ¬†and those before them? We destroyed them ЋєallЋЇ, ЋєforЋЇ they were truly wicked"
  44,38,We did not create the heavens and the earth and everything in between for sport
  44,39,"We only created them for a purpose, but most of these ЋєpagansЋЇ do not know"
  44,40,Surely the Day of ЋєFinalЋЇ Decision is the time appointed for allвАФ
  44,41,"the Day no kith or kin will be of benefit to another whatsoever, nor will they be helped"
  44,42,"except those shown mercy by God. He is truly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  44,43,Surely Ћєthe fruit ofЋЇ the tree of Zaqq√їm
  44,44,will be the food of the evildoer
  44,45,"Like molten metal, it will boil in the bellies"
  44,46,like the boiling of hot water
  44,47,"ЋєIt will be said,ЋЇ вАЬSeize them and drag them into the depths of the Hellfire"
  44,48,Then pour over their heads the torment of boiling water.вАЭ
  44,49,"ЋєThe wicked will be told,ЋЇ вАЬTaste this. You mighty, noble one"
  44,50,This is truly what you ЋєallЋЇ used to doubt.вАЭ
  44,51,"Indeed, the righteous will be in a secure place"
  44,52,amid Gardens and springs
  44,53,"dressed in fine silk and rich brocade, facing one another"
  44,54,So it will be. And We will pair them to maidens with gorgeous eyes
  44,55,There they will call for every fruit in serenity
  44,56,"There they will never taste death, beyond the first death. And He will protect them from the punishment of the HellfireвАФ"
  44,57,as Ћєan act ofЋЇ grace from your Lord. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the ultimate triumph
  44,58,"Indeed, We have made this ЋєQuranЋЇ easy in your own language ЋєO ProphetЋЇ so perhaps they will be mindful"
  44,59,Wait then! They too are certainly waiting
  45,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  45,2,"The revelation of this Book is from GodвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  45,3,Surely in Ћєthe creation ofЋЇ the heavens and the earth are signs for the believers
  45,4,"And in your own creation, and whatever living beings He dispersed, are signs for people of sure faith"
  45,5,"And ЋєinЋЇ the alternation of the day and the night, the provision¬†sent down from the skies by GodвАФreviving the earth after its deathвАФand the shifting of the winds, are signs for people of understanding"
  45,6,These are GodвАЩs revelations which We recite to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in truth. So what message will they believe in after ЋєdenyingЋЇ God and His revelations
  45,7,Woe to every sinful liar
  45,8,"They hear GodвАЩs revelations recited to them, then persist Ћєin denialЋЇ arrogantly as if they did not hear them. So give them good news of a painful punishment"
  45,9,"And whenever they learn anything of Our revelations, they make a mockery of it. It is they who will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  45,10,"Awaiting them is Hell. Their ЋєworldlyЋЇ gains will not be of any benefit to them whatsoever, nor will those protectors they have taken besides God. And they will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  45,11,This ЋєQuranЋЇ is ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance. And those who deny their LordвАЩs revelations will suffer the ЋєworstЋЇ torment of agonizing pain
  45,12,"God is the One Who has subjected the sea for you so that ships may sail upon it by His command, and that you may seek His bounty, and that perhaps you will be grateful"
  45,13,He ЋєalsoЋЇ subjected for you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earthвАФall by His grace. Surely in this are signs for people who reflect
  45,14,"ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ Tell the believers to forgive those who do not fear GodвАЩs days Ћєof tormentЋЇ, so that He will reward each group for what they used to commit"
  45,15,"Whoever does good, it is to their own benefit. And whoever does evil, it is to their own loss. Then to your Lord you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  45,16,"Indeed, We gave the Children of Israel the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood; granted them good, lawful provisions; and favoured them above the others"
  45,17,We ЋєalsoЋЇ gave them clear commandments regarding ЋєtheirЋЇ faith. But it was not until knowledge came to them that they differed out of mutual envy.¬†Surely your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their differences
  45,18,"Now We have set you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ on the ЋєclearЋЇ Way of faith. So follow it, and do not follow the desires of those who do not know Ћєthe truthЋЇ"
  45,19,"They certainly can be of no benefit to you against God whatsoever. Surely the wrongdoers are patrons of each other, whereas God is the Patron of the righteous"
  45,20,This ЋєQuranЋЇ is an insight for humanityвАФa guide and mercy for people of sure faith
  45,21,Or do those who commit evil deeds ЋєsimplyЋЇ think that We will make them equalвАФin their life and after their deathвАФto those who believe and do good? How wrong is their judgment
  45,22,"For God created the heavens and the earth for a purpose, so that every soul may be paid back for what it has committed. And none will be wronged"
  45,23,"Have you seen ЋєO ProphetЋЇ those who have taken their own desires as their god? ЋєAnd soЋЇ God left them to stray knowingly, sealed their hearing and hearts, and placed a cover on their sight. Who then can guide them after God? Will you ЋєallЋЇ not then be mindful"
  45,24,"And they argue, вАЬThere is nothing beyond our worldly life. We die;¬†others are born. And nothing destroys us but Ћєthe passage ofЋЇ time.вАЭ Yet they have no knowledge Ћєin supportЋЇ of this ЋєclaimЋЇ. They only speculate"
  45,25,"And whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, their only argument is to say: вАЬBring our forefathers back, if what you say is true!вАЭ"
  45,26,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬЋєIt isЋЇ God ЋєWhoЋЇ gives you life, then causes you to die, then will gather you ЋєallЋЇ on the Day of Judgment, about which there is no doubt. But most people do not know.вАЭ"
  45,27,"To God ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. On the Day the Hour will be established, the people of falsehood will then be in ЋєtotalЋЇ loss"
  45,28,"And you will see every faith-community on its knees. Every community will be summoned to its record Ћєof deedsЋЇ. ЋєThey all will be told,ЋЇ вАЬThis Day you will be rewarded for what you used to do"
  45,29,"This record of Ours speaks the truth about you. Indeed, We always had your deeds recorded Ћєby the angelsЋЇ.вАЭ"
  45,30,"As for those who believed and did good, their Lord will admit them into His mercy. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the absolute triumph"
  45,31,"And as for those who disbelieved, Ћєthey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬWere My revelations not recited to you, yet you acted arrogantly and were a wicked people"
  45,32,"And whenever it was said Ћєto youЋЇ, вАШSurely GodвАЩs promise Ћєof judgmentЋЇ is true and there is no doubt about the Hour,вАЩ you said ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАШWe do not know what the Hour is! We think it is no more than speculation, and we are not convinced Ћєthat it will ever comeЋЇ.вАЩвАЭ"
  45,33,"And the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of their deeds will unfold before them, and they will be overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  45,34,"It will be said, вАЬThis Day We will neglect you as you neglected the meeting of this Day of yours! Your home will be the Fire, and you will have no helpers"
  45,35,"This is because you made a mockery of GodвАЩs revelations, and were deluded by ЋєyourЋЇ worldly life.вАЭ So ЋєfromЋЇ that Day ЋєonЋЇ they will not be taken out of the Fire, nor will they be allowed to appease Ћєtheir LordЋЇ"
  45,36,"So all praise is for GodвАФLord of the heavens and Lord of the earth, Lord of all worlds"
  45,37,"To Him belongs ЋєallЋЇ Majesty in the heavens and the earth. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  46,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  46,2,"The revelation of this Book is from GodвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  46,3,We only created the heavens and the earth and everything in between for a purpose and an appointed term. Yet the disbelievers are turning away from what they have been warned about
  46,4,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬHave you considered whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you invoke besides God? Show me what they have created on earth! Or do they have a share in Ћєthe creation ofЋЇ the heavens? Bring me a scripture ЋєrevealedЋЇ before this ЋєQuranЋЇ or a shred of knowledge, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  46,5,"And who could be more astray than those who call upon others besides GodвАФЋєothersЋЇ that cannot respond to them until the Day of Judgment, and are ЋєevenЋЇ unaware of their calls"
  46,6,"And when ЋєsuchЋЇ people will be gathered together, those ЋєgodsЋЇ will be their enemies and will disown their worship"
  46,7,"Whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, the disbelievers say of the truth when it has come to them, вАЬThis is pure magic.вАЭ"
  46,8,"Or do they say, вАЬHe¬†has fabricated this ЋєQuranЋЇ!вАЭ? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf I have done so, then there is nothing whatsoever you can do to save me from God. He knows best what ЋєslursЋЇ you indulge about it. Sufficient is He as a Witness between you and me. And He is the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  46,9,"Say, вАЬI am not the first messenger ever sent, nor do I know what will happen to me or you. I only follow what is revealed to me. And I am only sent with a clear warning.вАЭ"
  46,10,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬConsider if this ЋєQuranЋЇ is ЋєtrulyЋЇ from God and you deny it, and a witness from the Children of Israel attests to it and then believes,¬†whereas you act arrogantly. Surely God does not guide the wrongdoing people.вАЭ"
  46,11,"The disbelievers say of the believers, вАЬHad it been ЋєsomethingЋЇ good, they¬†would not have beaten us to it.вАЭ Now since they reject its guidance, they will say, вАЬЋєThis isЋЇ an ancient fabrication!вАЭ"
  46,12,"And before this ЋєQuranЋЇ the Book of Moses was Ћєrevealed asЋЇ a guide and mercy. And this Book is a confirmation, in the Arabic tongue, to warn those who do wrong, and as good news to those who do good"
  46,13,"Surely those who say, вАЬOur Lord is God,вАЭ and then remain steadfastвАФthere will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  46,14,"It is they who will be the residents of Paradise, staying there forever, as a reward for what they used to do"
  46,15,"We have commanded people to honour their parents. Their mothers bore them in hardship and delivered them in hardship. Their Ћєperiod ofЋЇ bearing and weaning is thirty months. In time, when the child reaches their prime at the age of forty, they pray, вАЬMy Lord! Inspire me to ЋєalwaysЋЇ be thankful for Your favours which You blessed me and my parents with, and to do good deeds that please You. And instil righteousness in my offspring. I truly repent to You, and I truly submit Ћєto Your WillЋЇ.вАЭ"
  46,16,"It is from these ЋєpeopleЋЇ that We will accept the good they did, and overlook their misdeedsвАФalong with the residents of Paradise, Ћєin fulfilment ofЋЇ the true promise they have been given"
  46,17,"But some scold their parents, вАЬEnough with you! Are you warning me that I will be brought forth Ћєfrom the graveЋЇ, while many generations had already perished before me Ћєfor goodЋЇ?вАЭ The parents cry to God for help, Ћєand warn their child,ЋЇ вАЬPity you. Have faith! Surely GodвАЩs promise is true.вАЭ But the deniers insist, вАЬThis is nothing but ancient fables.вАЭ"
  46,18,"These are the ones against whom the fate of earlier communities of jinn and humans has been justified, ЋєforЋЇ they were truly losers"
  46,19,Each Ћєof the two groupsЋЇ will be ranked according to what they have done so He may fully reward all. And none will be wronged
  46,20,"ЋєWatch forЋЇ the Day ЋєwhenЋЇ the disbelievers will be exposed to the Fire. ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬYou ЋєalreadyЋЇ exhausted your Ћєshare ofЋЇ pleasures during your worldly life, and ЋєfullyЋЇ enjoyed them. So Today you will be rewarded with the torment of disgrace for your arrogance throughout the land with no right, and for your rebelliousness.вАЭ"
  46,21,"And remember the brother of вАЩ»Вd, when he warned his people, who inhabited the sand-hillsвАФthere were certainly warners before and after himвАФЋєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬWorship none but God. I truly fear for you the torment of a tremendous day.вАЭ"
  46,22,"They argued, вАЬHave you come to turn us away from our gods? Bring us then whatever you threaten us with, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  46,23,"He responded, вАЬThe knowledge Ћєof its timeЋЇ is only with God. I only convey to you what I have been sent with. But I can see that you are a people acting ignorantly.вАЭ"
  46,24,"Then when they saw the torment as a ЋєdenseЋЇ cloud approaching their valleys, they said ЋєhappilyЋЇ, вАЬThis is a cloud bringing us rain.вАЭ ЋєBut H√їd replied,ЋЇ вАЬNo, it is what you sought to hasten: a ЋєfierceЋЇ wind carrying a painful punishment!вАЭ"
  46,25,"It destroyed everything by the command of its Lord, leaving nothing visible except their ruins. This is how We reward the wicked people"
  46,26,"Indeed, We had established them¬†in a way We have not established you ЋєMeccansЋЇ. And We gave them hearing, sight, and intellect. But neither their hearing, sight, nor intellect were of any benefit to them whatsoever, since they persisted in denying GodвАЩs signs. And ЋєsoЋЇ they were overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  46,27,We certainly destroyed the societies around you after having varied the signs so perhaps they would return Ћєto the Right PathЋЇ
  46,28,"Why then did those ЋєidolsЋЇ they took as godsвАФhoping to get closer Ћєto HimЋЇвАФnot come to their aid? Instead, they failed them. That is Ћєthe result ofЋЇ their lies and their fabrications"
  46,29,"ЋєRemember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when We sent a group of jinn your way to listen to the Quran. Then, upon hearing it, they said Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬListen quietly!вАЭ Then when it was over, they returned to their fellow jinn as warners"
  46,30,"They declared, вАЬO our fellow jinn! We have truly heard a scripture revealed after Moses, confirming what came before it. It guides to the truth and the Straight Way"
  46,31,"O our fellow jinn! Respond to the caller of God and believe in him, He will forgive your sins and protect you from a painful punishment"
  46,32,"And whoever does not respond to the caller of God will have no escape on earth, nor will they have any protectors against Him. It is they who are clearly astray.вАЭ"
  46,33,"Do they not realize that God, Who created the heavens and the earth and did not tire in creating them,¬†is able to give life to the dead? Yes ЋєindeedЋЇ! He is certainly Most Capable of everything"
  46,34,"And on the Day the disbelievers will be exposed to the Fire, Ћєthey will be asked,ЋЇ вАЬIs this ЋєHereafterЋЇ not the truth?вАЭ They will cry, вАЬAbsolutely, by our Lord!вАЭ It will be said, вАЬThen taste the punishment for your disbelief.вАЭ"
  46,35,"So endure patiently, as did the Messengers of Firm Resolve.¬†And do not Ћєseek toЋЇ hasten Ћєthe tormentЋЇ for the deniers. On the Day they see what they have been threatened with, it will be as if they had only stayed Ћєin this worldЋЇ for an hour of a day.¬†ЋєThis isЋЇ a ЋєsufficientЋЇ warning! Then, will anyone be destroyed except the rebellious people"
  47,1,"Those who disbelieve and hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of God, He will render their deeds void"
  47,2,"As for those who believe, do good, and have faith in what has been revealed to MuбЄ•ammadвАФwhich is the truth from their LordвАФHe will absolve them of their sins and improve their condition"
  47,3,"This is because the disbelievers follow falsehood, while the believers follow the truth from their Lord. This is how God shows people their true state Ћєof faithЋЇ"
  47,4,"So when you meet the disbelievers Ћєin battleЋЇ, strike ЋєtheirЋЇ necks until you have thoroughly subdued them, then bind them firmly. Later Ћєfree them either asЋЇ an act of grace or by ransom until the war comes to an end. So will it be. Had God willed, He ЋєHimselfЋЇ could have inflicted punishment on them. But He does Ћєthis only toЋЇ test some of you by means of others. And those who are martyred in the cause of God,¬†He will never render their deeds void"
  47,5,"He will guide them Ћєto their rewardЋЇ, improve their condition"
  47,6,"and admit them into Paradise, having made it known to them"
  47,7,"O believers! If you stand up for God, He will help you and make your steps firm"
  47,8,"As for the disbelievers, may they be doomed and may He render their deeds void"
  47,9,"That is because they detest what God has revealed, so He has rendered their deeds void"
  47,10,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those before them? God annihilated them, and a similar fate awaits the disbelievers"
  47,11,This is because God is the Patron of the believers while the disbelievers have no patron
  47,12,"Surely God will admit those who believe and do good into Gardens under which rivers flow. As for the disbelievers, they enjoy themselves and feed like cattle.¬†But the Fire will be their home"
  47,13,"ЋєImagine, O Prophet,ЋЇ how many societies We destroyed that were far superior in might than your societyвАФwhich drove you outвАФand there was none to help them"
  47,14,Can those ЋєbelieversЋЇ who stand on clear proof from their Lord be like those whose evil deeds are made appealing to them and ЋєonlyЋЇ follow their desires
  47,15,"The description of the Paradise promised to the righteous is that in it are rivers of fresh water, rivers of milk that never changes in taste, rivers of wine delicious to drink, and rivers of pure honey. There they will ЋєalsoЋЇ have all kinds of fruit, and forgiveness from their Lord. ЋєCan they beЋЇ like those who will stay in the Fire forever, left to drink boiling water that will tear apart their insides"
  47,16,"There are some of them who listen to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, but when they depart from you, they say ЋєmockinglyЋЇ to those ЋєbelieversЋЇ gifted with knowledge, вАЬWhat did he just say?вАЭ These are the ones whose hearts God has sealed and who ЋєonlyЋЇ follow their desires"
  47,17,"As for those who are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided, He increases them in guidance and blesses them with righteousness"
  47,18,"Are they only waiting for the Hour to take them by surprise? Yet Ћєsome ofЋЇ its signs have already come.¬†Once it actually befalls them, will it not be too late to be mindful"
  47,19,"So, know Ћєwell, O Prophet,ЋЇ that there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except God. And seek forgiveness for your shortcomings¬†and for Ћєthe sins ofЋЇ the believing men and women. For God ЋєfullyЋЇ knows your movements and places of rest ЋєO peopleЋЇ"
  47,20,"And the believers say, вАЬIf only a s√їrah¬†was revealed Ћєallowing self-defenceЋЇ!вАЭ Yet when a precise s√їrah¬†is revealed, in which fighting is ЋєexplicitlyЋЇ mentioned, you see those with sickness in their hearts staring at you like someone in the throes of death. It would have been better for them"
  47,21,"to obey and speak rightly. Then when fighting was ordained, it surely would have been better for them if they were true to God"
  47,22,"Now if you ЋєhypocritesЋЇ turn away, perhaps you would then spread corruption throughout the land and sever your Ћєties ofЋЇ kinship"
  47,23,"These are the ones who God has condemned, deafening them and blinding their eyes"
  47,24,Do they not then reflect on the Quran? Or are there locks upon their hearts
  47,25,"Indeed, those who relapse Ћєinto disbeliefЋЇ after ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance has become clear to them, Ћєit isЋЇ Satan ЋєthatЋЇ has tempted them, luring them with false hopes"
  47,26,"That is because they said ЋєprivatelyЋЇ to those who ЋєalsoЋЇ detest what God has revealed, вАЬWe will obey you in some matters.вАЭ¬†But God ЋєfullyЋЇ knows what they are hiding"
  47,27,"Then how ЋєhorribleЋЇ will it be when the angels take their souls, beating their faces and backs"
  47,28,"This is because they follow whatever displeases God and hate whatever pleases Him, so He has rendered their deeds void"
  47,29,Or do those with sickness in their hearts think that God will not Ћєbe able toЋЇ expose their malice
  47,30,"Had We willed, We could have truly shown them to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, and you would have certainly recognized them by their appearance. But you will surely recognize them by their tone of speech. And God ЋєfullyЋЇ knows your doings ЋєO peopleЋЇ"
  47,31,"We will certainly test you ЋєbelieversЋЇ until We prove those of you who ЋєtrulyЋЇ struggle Ћєin GodвАЩs causeЋЇ and remain steadfast, and reveal how you conduct yourselves"
  47,32,"Indeed, those who disbelieve, hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of God, and defy the Messenger after ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance has become clear to them; they will not harm God in the least, but He will render their deeds void"
  47,33,"O believers! Obey God and obey the Messenger, and do not let your deeds be in vain"
  47,34,"Surely those who disbelieve, hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of God, and then die as disbelievers; God will never forgive them"
  47,35,"So do not falter or cry for peace, for you will have the upper hand and God is with you. And He will never let your deeds go to waste"
  47,36,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement. But if you are faithful and mindful Ћєof GodЋЇ, He will grant you your ЋєfullЋЇ reward, and will not ask you Ћєto donate allЋЇ your wealth"
  47,37,"If He were to do so and pressure you, you would withhold and He would bring out your resentment"
  47,38,"Here you are, being invited to donate Ћєa littleЋЇ in the cause of God. Still some of you withhold. And whoever does so, it is only to their own loss. For God is the Self-Sufficient, whereas you stand in need Ћєof HimЋЇ. If you ЋєstillЋЇ turn away, He will replace you with another people. And they will not be like you"
  48,1,"Indeed, We have granted you a clear triumph ЋєO ProphetЋЇ"
  48,2,"so that God may forgive you for your past and future shortcomings,¬†perfect His favour upon you, guide you along the Straight Path"
  48,3,and so that God will help you tremendously
  48,4,"He is the One Who sent down serenity upon the hearts of the believers so that they may increase even more in their faith. To God ЋєaloneЋЇ belong the forces of the heavens and the earth. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  48,5,So He may admit believing men and women¬†into Gardens under which rivers flowвАФto stay there foreverвАФand absolve them of their sins. And that is a supreme achievement in the sight of God
  48,6,"Also Ћєso thatЋЇ He may punish hypocrite men and women and polytheistic men and women, who harbour evil thoughts of God.¬†May ill-fate befall them! God is displeased with them. He has condemned them and prepared for them Hell. What an evil destination"
  48,7,"To God ЋєaloneЋЇ belong the forces of the heavens and the earth. And God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  48,8,"Indeed, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ We have sent you as a witness, a deliverer of good news, and a warner"
  48,9,"so that you ЋєbelieversЋЇ may have faith in God and His Messenger, support and honour him, and glorify God morning and evening"
  48,10,"Surely those who pledge allegiance to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are actually pledging allegiance to God. GodвАЩs Hand is over theirs. Whoever breaks their pledge, it will only be to their own loss. And whoever fulfils their pledge to God, He will grant them a great reward"
  48,11,"The nomadic Arabs, who stayed behind, will say to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, вАЬWe were preoccupied with our wealth and families, so ask for forgiveness for us.вАЭ They say with their tongues what is not in their hearts. Say, вАЬWho then can stand between you and God in any way, if He intends harm or benefit for you? In fact, God is All-Aware of what you do"
  48,12,"The truth is: you thought that the Messenger and the believers would never return to their families again. And that was made appealing in your hearts. You harboured evil thoughts Ћєabout GodЋЇ, and ЋєsoЋЇ became a doomed people.вАЭ"
  48,13,"And whoever does not believe in God and His Messenger, then We surely have prepared for the disbelievers a blazing Fire"
  48,14,"To God ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  48,15,"Those who stayed behind will say, when you ЋєbelieversЋЇ set out to take the spoils of war, вАЬLet us accompany you.вАЭ They wish to change GodвАЩs promise.¬†Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬYou will not accompany us. This is what God has said before.вАЭ They will then say, вАЬIn fact, you are driven by jealousy against us!вАЭ¬†The truth is: they can hardly comprehend"
  48,16,"Say to nomadic Arabs, who stayed behind, вАЬYou will be called Ћєto fightЋЇ against a people of great might,¬†who you will fight unless they submit. If you then obey, God will grant you a fine reward. But if you turn away as you did before, He will inflict upon you a painful punishment.вАЭ"
  48,17,"There is no blame on the blind, or the disabled, or the sick Ћєfor staying behindЋЇ. And whoever obeys God and His Messenger will be admitted by Him into Gardens under which rivers flow. But whoever turns away will be subjected by Him to a painful punishment"
  48,18,"Indeed, God was pleased with the believers when they pledged allegiance to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ under the tree. He knew what was in their hearts, so He sent down serenity upon them and rewarded them with a victory at hand"
  48,19,"and many spoils of war they will gain. For God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  48,20,"God has promised you ЋєbelieversЋЇ abundant spoils, which you will gain, so He hastened this ЋєtruceЋЇ¬†for you. And He has held peopleвАЩs hands back from ЋєharmingЋЇ you, so it may be a sign for the believers, and so He may guide you along the Straight Path"
  48,21,And Ћєthere areЋЇ other gains which are beyond your reach that God is keeping in store Ћєfor youЋЇ. For God is Most Capable of everything
  48,22,"If the disbelievers were to fight you, they would certainly flee.¬†Then they would never find any protector or helper"
  48,23,"ЋєThis isЋЇ GodвАЩs way, already long established Ћєin the pastЋЇ. And you will find no change in GodвАЩs way"
  48,24,"He is the One Who held back their hands from you and your hands from them in the valley of ЋєбЄ§udaibiyah, nearЋЇ Mecca, after giving you the upper hand over Ћєa group ofЋЇ them.¬†And God is All-Seeing of what you do"
  48,25,"They are the ones who persisted in disbelief and hindered you from the Sacred Mosque, preventing the sacrificial animals from reaching their destination.¬†ЋєWe would have let you march through Mecca,ЋЇ had there not been believing men and women, unknown to you. You might have trampled them underfoot, incurring guilt for Ћєwhat you did toЋЇ them unknowingly. That was so God may admit into His mercy whoever He wills.¬†Had those ЋєunknownЋЇ believers stood apart, We would have certainly inflicted a painful punishment on the disbelievers"
  48,26,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the disbelievers had filled their hearts with prideвАФthe pride of Ћєpre-IslamicЋЇ ignoranceвАФthen God sent down His serenity upon His Messenger and the believers, inspiring them to uphold the declaration of faith,¬†for they were better entitled and more worthy of it. And God has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  48,27,"Indeed, God will fulfil His MessengerвАЩs vision in all truth: God willing, you will surely enter the Sacred Mosque, in securityвАФЋєsome withЋЇ heads shaved and Ћєothers withЋЇ hair shortenedвАФwithout fear.¬†He knew what you did not know, so He first granted you the triumph at hand"
  48,28,"He is the One Who has sent His Messenger with ЋєrightЋЇ guidance and the religion of truth, making it prevail over all others. And sufficient is God as a Witness"
  48,29,"MuбЄ•ammad is the Messenger of God. And those with him are firm with the disbelievers¬†and compassionate with one another. You see them bowing and prostrating¬†Ћєin prayerЋЇ, seeking GodвАЩs bounty and pleasure. The sign Ћєof brightness can be seenЋЇ on their faces from the trace of prostrating Ћєin prayerЋЇ. This is their description in the Torah.¬†And their parable in the Gospel is that of a seed that sprouts its ЋєtinyЋЇ branches, making it strong. Then it becomes thick, standing firmly on its stem, to the delight of the plantersвАФin this way God makes the believers a source of dismay for the disbelievers.¬†To those of them who believe and do good, God has promised forgiveness and a great reward"
  49,1,"O believers! Do not proceed Ћєin any matterЋЇ before Ћєa decree fromЋЇ God and His Messenger. And fear God. Surely God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  49,2,"O believers! Do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet, nor speak loudly to him as you do to one another,¬†or your deeds will become void while you are unaware"
  49,3,"Indeed, those who lower their voices in the presence of GodвАЩs Messenger are the ones whose hearts God has refined for righteousness. They will have forgiveness and a great reward"
  49,4,"Indeed, most of those who call out to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ from outside ЋєyourЋЇ private quarters have no understanding Ћєof mannersЋЇ"
  49,5,"Had they been patient until you could come out to them, it would have certainly been better for them. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  49,6,"O believers, if an evildoer brings you any news, verify ЋєitЋЇ so you do not harm people unknowingly, becoming regretful for what you have done"
  49,7,"And keep in mind that GodвАЩs Messenger is ЋєstillЋЇ in your midst. If he were to yield to you in many matters, you would surely suffer Ћєthe consequencesЋЇ.¬†But God has endeared faith to you, making it appealing in your hearts. And He has made disbelief, rebelliousness, and disobedience detestable to you. Those are the ones rightly guided"
  49,8,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a bounty and a blessing from God. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  49,9,"And if two groups of believers fight each other, then make peace between them. But if one of them transgresses against the other, then fight against the transgressing group until they Ћєare willing toЋЇ submit to the rule of God. If they do so, then make peace between both ЋєgroupsЋЇ in all fairness and act justly. Surely God loves those who uphold justice"
  49,10,"The believers are but one brotherhood, so make peace between your brothers. And be mindful of God so you may be shown mercy"
  49,11,"O believers! Do not let some ЋєmenЋЇ ridicule others, they may be better than them, nor let ЋєsomeЋЇ women ridicule other women, they may be better than them. Do not defame one another, nor call each other by offensive nicknames. How evil it is to act rebelliously after having faith! And whoever does not repent, it is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ wrongdoers"
  49,12,"O believers! Avoid many suspicions, ЋєforЋЇ indeed, some suspicions are sinful. And do not spy, nor backbite one another. Would any of you like to eat the flesh of their dead brother? You would despise that!¬†And fear God. Surely God is ЋєtheЋЇ Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  49,13,"O humanity! Indeed, We created you from a male and a female, and made you into peoples and tribes so that you may Ћєget toЋЇ know one another. Surely the most noble of you in the sight of God is the most righteous among you. God is truly All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  49,14,"ЋєSome ofЋЇ the nomadic Arabs say, вАЬWe believe.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬYou have not believed. But say, вАШWe have submitted,вАЩ for faith has not yet entered your hearts.¬†But if you obey God and His Messenger ЋєwholeheartedlyЋЇ, He will not discount anything from Ћєthe reward ofЋЇ your deeds. God is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  49,15,The ЋєtrueЋЇ believers are only those who believe in God and His MessengerвАФnever doubtingвАФand strive with their wealth and their lives in the cause of God. They are the ones true in faith
  49,16,"Say, вАЬDo you inform God of your faith, when God ЋєalreadyЋЇ knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth? And God has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things.вАЭ"
  49,17,"They regard their acceptance of Islam as a favour to you. Tell Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬDo not regard your Islam as a favour to me. Rather, it is God Who has done you a favour by guiding you to the faith, if ЋєindeedЋЇ you are faithful"
  49,18,Surely God knows the unseen of the heavens and earth. And God is All-Seeing of what you do.вАЭ